Title: Data Analyst
Description:
About Idelic

We are a venture-backed startup with a goal to fundamentally change the transportation industry. Our product, Safety Suite®, combines proprietary AI technology with modern UX principles to give trucking fleets an all-in-one platform to manage their drivers and bring them home safely each night. Our SaaS solutions have already helped fleets of all sizes unlock major improvements and change how they manage their drivers.

We believe people do their best work in an environment that reflects the five core values we hold ourselves to: Safety, innovation, collaboration, passion, and quality, so we look for team members that embody these values, too.

About Our Team

As a company, we are filled with passionate, creative people who seek to deliver the best experience for our clients. At Idelic, we’re committed to our mission, our customers, our teammates, and fostering a values-driven culture. We hire optimistic, results-oriented, innovative, and adaptable individuals with the desire to help our clients and one another succeed.

Overview

Of The Role

The Data Analyst works closely with key business stakeholders to inform company strategy and value to our customers. The Data Analyst is capable of high-level, strategic thinking to determine what questions should be explored but also has the necessary tactical skills to turn raw data into clear, presentable findings This role will be integrated into a team where they will work on challenging projects that will lead to safer roads and more efficient drivers and fleets.

What You’ll Do
Leverage internal and external data sets to conduct analysis for case studies, market research, white papers, product strategy, and more.
Interpret data to identify trends and opportunities for business, process, and product improvements.
Ensure data accuracy and integrity while also integrating data from multiple data sources and functional areas to perform complex analyses and evaluation.
Be responsible for answering the questions through hands-on analysis, including extracting data, running queries, light data visualization, etc. as well as determining the questions to ask through exploratory analysis, market research, and working with internal and external stakeholders.
Present work to senior leadership across the organization.
Work closely with stakeholders across senior leadership, product, data science, sales, customer success, and marketing to help inform strategy through analysis.
Work on any task and help solve problems when needed!
What You’ll Need To Succeed In The Role
3+ years of experience in Data Analysis
Experience conducting research and communicating results in clear, unbiased terms
Bachelor’s or equivalent degree in computer science, statistics, information science, economics, or a related field
Very comfortable with SQL
Comfortable with data visualization techniques to present ideas clearly (when to use different plots, what types of data visualization to avoid, etc.).
Comfortable with some BI, statistical and data visualization tooling (e.g. Tableau, Looker, R, Jupyter Notebook)
Analytical and Problem Solving Skills
Proven ability to work in a collaborative and fast-paced environment
What Will Set You Apart
A public portfolio of data analysis work
Experience with PostGresSQL in particular
Basic scripting (e.g. Python)
Experience working within ETL pipelines and developing ETL processes
Experience working in Commercial Trucking Industry or related fields
THINGS THAT MAKE IDELIC A GREAT PLACE TO WORK
Competitive Compensation Package Including Options
Unlimited Paid Time Off (PTO)
Medical, Dental, Vision, Disability and Life Insurance
401(k) with Company Matching Funds
Paid Parental Leave, Adoption Assistance, and Paid Military Leave

Be Part of a Small Team (to Start)— Which Translates To You Having A Big Personal Impact

Completionist - You have knowledge in the technical aspects of gaming platforms, as well as in F2P mobile games and the industry’s nascent trends. You have shipped and supported at least one successful mobile app.

Responsibilities

Expertly perform quantitative analysis and data interrogation to identify problems, understand our users, and help us make informed decisions, using SQL and our other analytics tools.
Respond to questions from the team, providing relevant data and visualizations to help lead the team to success.
Express your findings clearly and concisely through spoken words, text, charts/diagrams, and the occasional Slack GIF.
Operate independently and forge your own trail when necessary, refining and building new processes as needed.
Draw on prior industry experience and a knowledge of F2P games to inform your contributions to discussions and decisions.

The Perks

Unlimited PTO Policy - When it comes to sick and vacation days, we don’t believe in tracking the hours our employees work or don’t work. If you need to take time off — be it for date night, a vacation, or even just a personal wellness day — we support you. We go out of our way to create a guilt-free office environment. Our goal is simply to create incredible products, which we believe is best achieved when you don’t have a manager looming over your shoulder, tracking the minutes you are in or out.
Medical, Dental, and Vision Plans - We offer a generous yearly stipend, and have several premium plans available from major health care providers. Already have medical coverage? Keep the stipend as an end of year bonus.
Matching 401k - Send a portion of your salary towards retirement, and we’ll match a certain amount. Free money!
Well Stocked Kitchen - Healthy snacks, not-as-healthy (but arguably tastier) snacks, and beverages are supplied to keep you going throughout the day (when we all eventually return to the office).
Frequent Celebrations - We work hard, but we like to let off steam, too. You’ll find us playing board games, video games, trivia, and even the occasional field trip to an escape room or other attraction around the city, all courtesy of Hidden Variable. 

Equal Opportunities

We believe diverse backgrounds and life experiences enable us to collectively build better and more inclusive games. We encourage applications from candidates from any background who are eager to celebrate their unique perspective.


How to Apply?

Hopefully, by the time you’ve scrolled this far, you’ve realized that we value high quality products and people who are passionate about what they do for a living.

Ready to apply? Please send us an email with your resume, a cover letter, and if applicable, a portfolio. List the position you’re applying for in the subject line and send us a message at careers@hiddenvariable.com. We can’t wait to hear from you!

For more details, visit here: https://www.hiddenvariable.com/careers/data-analyst/

Title: Data Analyst
Description:
Synthetic Genomics, Inc. (SGI) is growing algae biofuels to one day power planes, propel ships and fuel trucks—ultimately offering the potential to cut carbon emissions in half. SGI’s research spans from developing genetically engineered algae strains to cultivating acres of energy-rich algae at our state-of-the-art farm in California’s Imperial Valley. At the center of this research is SGI’s Integrated Data Platform, which is responsible for the automated collection and analysis of sensor data and sophisticated laboratory measurements. SGI’s Integrated Data Platform provides a common operating picture that fosters cross team collaborations and provides an increased understanding of the factors driving performance variation across the scales from lab to farm. 

To enhance SGI’s ability to make data driven decisions and reduce time to actionable insights, SGI is looking for a Data Analyst to join its Integrated Data Platform team. As a Data Analyst, you will work with a variety of datasets to develop new metrics of performance and implement analysis techniques to meet business, operational and research needs. In this role, you will work along-side experienced data professionals (e.g., Data Scientists, Data Engineers) and partner with laboratory and field scientists. We are looking for an inquisitive data analyst with passion for all things data and the desire to learn from top researchers in their respective fields.
Responsibilities
Interpret data, analyze results using statistical techniques and provide ongoing reports
Identify, analyze, and interpret trends or patterns in complex data sets
Define key performance indicators (KPIs) to measure the effectiveness of new algal strains and outdoor cultivation techniques 
Develop techniques to improve data quality
Acquire data from primary or secondary data sources and develop data requirements for automating ingestion and processing
Qualifications
Bachelors Degree in Mathematics, Statistics, Operations Research or similar field with 5+ years of experience in an analytics position in academia, government or industry
Or
Masters Degree in Statistics, Data Science, Mathematics or similar field with 2+ years of experience in an analytics position in academia, government or industry
Key Skills
Experience with one or more mathematical/statistical programs: Matlab, R, SAS, JMP, SPSS, etc.
Beginning to intermediate knowledge of SQL with ability to increase proficiency to an advanced level
Ability to use dashboarding technologies (Tableau, Qlik, PowerBI, etc.) to provide consumer-ready insights and reporting 
Strong problem solving skills
Enjoys working all aspects of data analysis:    analyzing, organizing, improving quality and reporting

Title: Data Analyst
Company: CUNY Institute for State & Local Governance
Description:
About Us

The CUNY Institute for State and Local Governance has a mission to improve the financing, delivery, and measurement of critical public services through research, technical assistance, and education. We lead projects aimed at reforming the criminal justice system, measuring urban inequality, expanding the reach of social service providers, and more. Each project has a dedicated team of research and policy experts who collaborate closely with internal and external organizations. Our staff have the opportunity to work with colleagues and supervisors across projects and with different types of expertise. We are seeking new team members with enthusiasm to shape the future of state and local policy.

Our goals for diversity and inclusion

We strive to foster an office environment and an approach to work that welcomes and respects different perspectives, backgrounds, and life experiences. We are working towards our goal of recruiting and retaining staff and board members who are diverse in terms of race, national origin, sexual orientation, gender identity or expression, age, religion, veteran status, socioeconomic status, disability, and justice system involvement.

Who We Are Looking For

We are hiring a Data Analyst to work on multiple projects, with key responsibilities in the collection, cleaning, and management of data.

This is an excellent opportunity for a civic-minded professional interested in a public policy environment. ISLG’s research projects span government policymaking in New York City and nationally, and cover a number of areas including criminal justice, racial equity, infrastructure and transportation, government operations, and finance.

The Data Analyst will work on a range of tasks which may include but are not limited to:

Data Management
Writing programing and syntax to import, validate, normalize, merge, restructure, and clean case-level administrative data files for analysis at the direction of a research team
Creating and maintaining data repositories and other data collection systems
Maintaining detailed documentation on data management decisions and technical work
Developing codebooks, file specifications, and other resource documents
Working closely with research staff to ensure that technical work is informed by an understanding of local policy context
Working with partners to extract data from data warehouses and other back-end systems
Conducting administrative data and systems reviews
Data Presentation and Visualization
Supporting the creation of data visualizations and dashboards
Developing data feeds and automated reporting
Our office is located in New York City and the position will be housed there over the long-term, however, work will be remote through the immediate term.

We Would Love To Hear From You If
You have a BA degree in computer science, data analytics, data science, data/information management, economics, or related field
You have some data management and analysis experience
You are familiar with cleaning, coding, merging, and analyzing large and complex quantitative data files in Python, R, and/or SQL
You have some experience collecting and working with administrative data, particularly data from government agencies (experience with criminal justice data a plus)
You can discuss technical work with project members in an accessible manner
You have excellent time management skills and experience working in deadline-driven environments
You can prioritize and work on a number of tasks simultaneously
You have an exceptional commitment to accuracy and attention to detail
You are flexible
This is a full-time position in New York City with a salary range of $50,000-$80,000 and excellent benefits, including:
Comprehensive medical/dental/vision insurance
Paid vacation and personal days
Paid sick leave
CUNY tuition reimbursement program
Pre-tax benefits for transit and healthcare costs
Family/parental leave
Life insurance
A retirement plan with employer contribution.
Our Staff Also Benefit From
A positive work/life balance
Opportunities for advancement within the organization
Engagement with the broader CUNY network
Working with organizational leadership who have years of significant public sector and policymaking expertise
How To Apply

To apply for please visit https://www.rfcuny.org/careers/postings?pvnID=VB-2104-003982. You will need to submit a cover letter describing your qualifications and interests and attach your curriculum vitae. Questions about the position can be addressed to info@islg.cuny.edu. Application review will commence immediately and continue until the position is filled.

The CUNY Institute for State and Local Governance and the Research Foundation of the City University of New York are an Affirmative Action/Equal Opportunity/Americans with Disabilities Act/Protected Veterans Status/ E-Verify Employer

Title: Data Analyst
Description:
Who is Duke’s?

Duke’s is a dynamic, growing business that specializes in services and products for the municipal water and wastewater industry. With over 300 million miles of pipes serviced, we focus on improving the wastewater/stormwater collection system through our innovative and cost-effective inspection, maintenance, and repair services. With long-standing customers across the country, and the continued growing need to solve our nation’s infrastructure problems, Duke’s is looking to continue growing our team.

This position is currently located at our Crystal Lake, IL, office but moving to Elgin, IL, late summer of 2021.

What To Expect

The Data Analyst is responsible for reviewing data and turning that into informative reports that are the final deliverables for our clients. Data Analysts are exceptional at finding patterns in data and creating additional queries and visualizations on the fly and has a keen attention to detail in the production of professional write ups and reports. Some key responsibilities include:
Develop client facing dashboards and reports that summarize data collected from professional water and wastewater surveys that we perform in the field. Key clients for deliverables are Professional Engineers and Utility Directors and Managers.
Integrate and merge data across multiple tool platforms.
Produce engaging, concise and understandable written reports for our clients.
Manipulate data over our in-house GIS platform
Participate in pre-construction and deliverables meetings as required.
What We Are Looking For
Bachelor’s degree in Engineering, Business Analytics, Economics or related field; equivalent work experience may be considered.
Proven experience in data mining and analysis.
Critical thinking skills and computer-based problem-solving skills are a must, even working with new software applications and data sets.
Strong communication skills, both written and verbal. Must be able to write and speak clearly to communicate complex data into easy-to-understand information.
Experience producing professional reports, executive summary write ups, and Power Point presentations.
Attention to detail, must be able to understand the data and identify trends to ensure correct conclusions.
Strength in math skills and statistics
Experience with applications such as Access (VBA), SQL (including writing stored procedures), Tableau/MS Power BI and/or Excel (VBA/macros production) is required. Applicants will undergo a skills assessment for knowledge in this category.
GIS experience is preferred, but not required.

Duke’s Root Control, Inc. complies with applicable state and local laws governing non-discrimination in employment in every location in which the company has facilities. 5/2021

Duke’s Root Control has been serving the underground pipeline industry with continued excellence since 1948. Back in 1979, we also saw a need to help solve root control problems in our sewer pipelines and became trailblazers in the industry by perfecting chemical root control services and performing quality manhole and pipeline assessment/rehabilitation services.

Increase veracity (trustworthiness) of data by suggesting opportunities for improvement
Promote the value of data by suggesting, creating, and supporting innovation activities

Work with Product Owners to identify new product onboarding opportunities
Ensure the Data Access Request process is optimized to facilitate access provisioning

Title: Data Analyst - Creator Economics

Launched in 2011, Twitch is a global community that comes together each day to create multiplayer entertainment: unique, live, unpredictable experiences created by the interactions of millions. Experience building aggregates and optimizing data workstreams

Passion about online communities, games, and Twitch

Description:
Roofstock is the leading marketplace for investing in single-family rental homes. Our mission is to make real estate investing radically accessible, cost effective and simple. We want to use technology to transform the way real estate is bought and sold and make real estate investing as simple as investing in stocks. Simply put, we are passionate about helping our customers build wealth through real estate.

Roofstock has been recognized as a Great Place to Work® and was recently named to the Forbes Fintech 50 and the Red Herring 100 lists of most innovative companies. Roofstock has raised over $135M to date, is based in Oakland, California and Dallas,Texas with approximately 180 people and is growing rapidly. Within Owner Services, the Growth team iterates quickly and leverages the Roofstock data platform to deliver meaningful insights and engaging user experiences for our users. Title: Data Analyst
Description:
Company Overview

Cohere Health is illuminating healthcare for patients, their doctors, and all those who are important in a patient’s healthcare experience, both in and out of the doctors office. Founded in August, 2019, we are obsessed with eliminating wasteful friction patients and doctors experience in areas that have nothing to do with health and treatment, particularly for diagnoses that require expensive procedures or medications. To that end, we build software that is expressly designed to ensure the appropriate plan of care is understood and expeditiously approved, so that patients and doctors can focus on health, rather than payment or administrative hassles.

Opportunity Overview

We are looking for a Data Analyst to come join our awesome team. As the Data Analyst, your responsibility will be to make sure data in our platform is validated, cleaned and ready for any reporting and analytics work. You will work closely with the analytics, clinical content, product and engineering to understand the data needs, validate ETL summary reports, monitor jobs and troubleshooting on issues. The work will be fast-paced and project-based, with evolving needs - requiring scrappiness, flexibility, curiosity, and grace under pressure.

At a growing organization, this is a position that offers the ability to make a substantive mark on the company and its partners with exponential growth opportunity. You will be part of the data management team and build one Cohere data platform to support our downstream teams to optimize patient care paths.

What You Will Do

Quickly understand Cohere’s products, services and clinical programs and how Cohere’s x-functional collaboration and workflow support healthcare providers’ workflow and patients’ care journey
Work with business analysts to understand what data we have and monitor production jobs
Ensure data quality, for example:
Monitor daily refresh data jobs from payer to our Cohere platform and from Cohere platform to our data platform
Perform and review quality checks on incoming, outgoing and aggregated data in order to identify data anomalies.
Map and specify target data requirements and associated data transformations and validations
Your Background & Requirements

1-2 years data experience at company where health outcomes were critical to the mission, preferably a healthcare analytics company or population health organization
Passionate about improving the U.S. healthcare system and helping ensure every patient receives the best care possible.
Self-starter, able to work independently, able to succeed in a fast-paced, high intensity start-up environment
Strong analysis and validation skills
Strong interest and understanding of EMR data, Claims and SDOH data
Strong Excel and other MS Office tools skills
Proficient in R, SQL, Python, Scala, AWS (S3, Airflow, Athena, Spark)
Excellent interpersonal skills to work with end users to develop QC metrics
Knowledge of STARs, HEDIS and other clinical / financial metrics in healthcare
We can’t wait to learn more about you and meet you at Cohere Health!

Equal Opportunity Statement

Cohere Health is an Equal Opportunity Employer. We are committed to fostering an environment of mutual respect where equal employment opportunities are available to all. To us, it’s personal.

Title: Entry Level Data Scientist
Description:
Toyota Connected's Mobility team is responsible for building and managing our connected vehicle platforms, supporting product research using vehicle sensor data and creating new and exciting data services for Toyota customers that makes driving safer, more convenient, and fun. We're looking for an Entry Level Data Scientist interested in using data science and statistical techniques to create state-of-the-art solutions for non-trivial, and arguably, unsolved problems. If you are results driven, interested in how to apply advanced Data Science techniques, would love to work with vehicle telemetry data and video, are highly innovative and long for the opportunity to build solutions for challenging problems that directly impact the company's bottom-line, we want to talk to you.

What will you be doing?

You will have the opportunity to work in a fast-paced Agile Scrum environment to assist in prototyping, designing, and implementing predictive models and algorithms to create real world solutions
Execute full modeling life cycle including data cleansing, feature creation and iterative model selection
Perform data analysis and derive meaningful insights from a variety of data sources
Write maintainable, extensible, tested code, while complying with coding standards
Produce specifications and determine operation feasibility
Troubleshoot, debug, and upgrade existing systems

Qualifications:

You want to make things work. Coming up with creative solutions comes naturally to you and you're comfortable being set loose without a lot of direction
You show a sense of ownership and pride in what you do, and you can make us believe you'll excel
You can easily point to multiple activities and projects that demonstrate how you go above and beyond
You're able to show empathy and work in a team environment
You have the ability to work well in a team oriented, Agile software engineering environment
You have the ability to write clean, concise, tested, maintainable code in Python, Java, Scala, C#, C++, Go, or Ruby
You show a strong desire to work in Data Science
You have a Bachelor or Master's degree in Computer Science, Data Science, Machine Learning, or related discipline; or have equivalent experience

What's in it for you?

In addition to an excellent compensation and benefits package, you'll also receive:

A Career Path that allows you to take your career to the next level.
Annual $2,000 Training Budget to help you grow and develop.
Unlimited time off and flexibility for a great worklife balance. At TC you'll be treated like the professional we know you are and left to manage your own time and work load.
Four months of paid parental leave. We want new moms and dads to have an opportunity to bond with their new little bundles of joy.
401(k) with generous company match that is fully vested Day One.
Toyota and Lexus vehicle discounts to allow you to drive in style.
Annual Patent-a-thons and Hackathons to embrace your superior creative thinking ability.
Annual gym membership reimbursement. We have a Toyota Connected fit club that loves plank competitions!
Free catered lunches every day. We try to keep it healthy, but Fridays are "cheat" days, so you can get your carbs on!
Two fully stocked Nespresso bars for your coffee and tea fixes.
Stocked kitchens with healthy snacks including fresh fruit, almonds, mixed nuts, pretzels, trail mix, and flavored waters. Nobody is hangry here!
Fun game room for the gamer that lives inside you! Xbox, virtual reality, and Nintendo Switch gamers live here and are always ready for their next opponent.
No dress code! Come as you are. We know the smart people we hire don't need to be told what to wear.
Free covered garage parking to shield your vehicle from those sneaky storms and to protect your buns from the Texas sun.

Who Are We?

Toyota Connected is a new company created to infuse the power of big data and cloud intelligence into all aspects of the mobility experience so that driving a Toyota or Lexus is more personal, intuitive and safe. We create and enable technologies that delight, simplify and connect the lives of those who use our products. We believe this mobility revolution will empower our customers to use their vehicles in an array of exciting new ways. We support, celebrate and thrive on the opportunity to provide Mobility for All.

Making a connected life a more human experience takes humans from all walks of life. Toyota Connected celebrates and is committed to a diverse and inclusive workplace that embraces you regardless of your race, gender, religion, sexual orientation, skin color, age, disability, military or veteran status, big shot relative, or Instagram fame. Different makes us awesome.

Title: Junior Modeling and Data Analyst
Description:
Position Description

If you love modeling and data analysis planning supporting the Federal Emergency Management Agency (FEMA), Serco has a great opportunity for you! This Junior Modeling Data Analyst will be on a dynamic team using your experience and expertise.

This position is contingent upon your ability to obtain/maintain/transfer at a minimum DHS Public Trust Clearance.

This position is contingent upon contract award.

This position is contingent customer approval.

Serco supports the National Planning Branch, Regional Planning Branch, Incident Support Planning Branch, and the National Hurricane Program (NHP) within the PED, and Response, Recovery and other FEMA mission area/functional planning requirements.

You will be part of a 3-4+ person Team at a minimum that works closely with the customer and other Serco Team members.

In This Role You Will
Compile Excel spreadsheets and using Visual Basic for Applications to make data visible before analysis
Maintain databases or data systems, as well as identifying new process improvement opportunities.
Utilize programmatic and quantitative methods to identify patterns and relationships in large data sets, as well as apply mathematical, statistical, and other data-driven analysis to address intelligence questions.
Involves coding and re-coding data contained within various databases to identify patterns.
Create visualizations, including dashboards, flowcharts, and graphs to relay business concepts through visuals to colleagues and other relevant stakeholders.
Responsible for performing quantitative analysis of complex business situations, such as strategies, performance, and solutions involving sales and customer performance.

Qualifications

To be successful in this role, you will have:
Bachelor's Degree in a related field
A United States Citizenship
The ability to obtain/maintain/or transfer at a minimum a DHS FEMA Public Trust
The ability to deploy to any location in the United States with a 24-48 hour notice.
The ability to deploy for 6 months – 12 months
Programming experience in one or more languages (Python, Java, R, SAS, SPSS, etc.), especially experience in data formatting and database management (MySQL, MongoDB, Hadoop MapReduce or other big data frameworks) or web application design (JavaScript, HTML/CSS).
One (1) years and one (1) year progressively more responsible experience in the support of emergency management modeling and data related projects.
One (1) years demonstrated experience in the application of social science research and evaluation methods in support of emergency management operational decision-making.
One (1) years performing quantitative and qualitative analysis in emergency management policies, programs, and procedures supporting federal agencies.

Additional Desired Experience And Skills
An active DHS FEMA Public Trust Clearance
If you are interested in supporting and working with our Civil Emergency efforts then submit your application now for immediate consideration. It only takes a few minutes and could change your career!

Company Overview

Serco Inc. (Serco) is the Americas division of Serco Group, plc. Serco serves every branch of the U.S. military, numerous U.S. Federal civilian agencies, the Intelligence Community, the Canadian government, state and local governments, and commercial clients. We help our clients deliver vital services more efficiently while increasing the satisfaction of their end customers. Headquartered in Herndon, Virginia, Serco Americas has approximately 8,000 employees and is part of a $4 billion global business that helps transform government and public services around the world. At Serco, our employees are our most valuable asset - we listen, respect and support them throughout their career at Serco. We invite you to become part of our dynamic team. Serco is an equal opportunity employer committed to diversifying our workforce (Race/ Color/ Sex/ Sexual Orientation/ Gender Identity/ Religion/ National Origin/ Disability/ Vets).

Title: Data Analyst
Description:
About AcreTrader
AcreTrader launched in 2018 and has established itself as a leader in the farmland investment industry. Our team and company have grown at an incredible pace, and in order to continue this growth, we must do so intentionally. We have very high expectations for ourselves, each other, and every new team member. We’re looking for high performers who go about their work with a sense of curiosity and a drive to make things better. Submit an application if you would like to be part of a fast moving operation with an opportunity to make a massive impact at the intersection of finance, technology, and agriculture.

AcreTrader is a real estate investing platform that makes it easy to buy shares of farmland and earn passive income. United States farmland has historically outperformed most asset classes and other forms of real estate. Unfortunately, buying and maintaining farmland directly is extremely difficult without local knowledge, management, and large investment commitments. AcreTrader solves these issues by providing transparency, flexibility, and ease of use to people wanting to invest in farmland while handling all aspects of administration and property management, from insurance and accounting to working with local farmers and improving soil sustainability.

Data Analyst
AcreTrader is seeking an employee to work with our technology team to help lead data entry and hygiene efforts. This person will help with organizing our data gathering and cleaning efforts alongside a senior team of data scientists and geospatial analysts. Information will be gathered via pdf retrieval, phone calls, web monitoring, and working with our farm analyst and geospatial engineering teams. 

Candidates would be working within a startup environment that requires flexibility and nimbleness with good communication skills and willingness to make a real contribution to the team. As with any growing company, many other tasks and responsibilities should be expected to be assigned as well as growth opportunities to be seized. 

Key Outcomes
Assist AcreTrader’s data gathering and organization efforts
Input comparable sales information from various sources into AcreTrader’s proprietary data analysis and mapping tools
Drive data hygiene and updating efforts to ensure 100% accuracy of various data collection efforts and methodologies 
Nurture ideas and solutions to existing customer problems utilizing feedback and data analysis
Audit information and recognize data issues and inconsistencies
Enhance data science team efforts for growth and analysis of proprietary datasets
Work with data scientists and financial analysts to determine most useful data fields and mapping based on geographic area
Work with data science team and engineering teams to optimize outcomes and workflow development
Coordinate with other AcreTrader team members to ensure that customers needs are met

Within 30 days develop a deep understanding of AcreTrader’s business and customer offerings
Be able to make informed presentations to internal stakeholders
Begin providing targets and current performance on a bi-monthly basis to management

Understand AcreTrader’s mission and core values
Maintain a high level of integrity
Clearly articulate the vision for AcreTrader as well as the core beliefs of the company
Be able to defend thoughts and ideas internally in a professional manner when challenged

Key Competencies/Requirements
Intellectually curious
Dogged in pursuit of goals
Exceptional attention to details
Previous working experience with data input and organization 
Outstanding communication, presentation and leadership skills
Excellent organizational and time management skills
Sharp analytical and problem-solving skills
Ability to manage a large and diverse workload 
Fayetteville, AR based

Title: Data Analyst
Description:
Under the direction of the VP Pricing and Merchandising Solutions the Data Analyst (Omni Pricing) will work closely and collaboratively with the merchandising, marketing, E-Commerce, and Retail Operations teams. He/She will analyze and interpret robust data sets to develop pricing strategies that will determine optimal price points and achieve sales and earnings goals in an Omni setting, while managing impact on Retail and E-Commerce. While He/She will focus on developing and implementing Omni pricing strategies with the supporting analytical rigor to ensure beneficial outcome for Retail, E-commerce, and Commercial. The individual will be focused on but not limited to the following.

Responsibilities
Collect and maintain tracking of competitive price checks and price indices by market and competitor
Conduct analysis and make pricing recommendations on similar products and services across key competitors while accounting for strength and size differences across like-products
Develop and maintain pricing tools including competitive tracking, elasticity and costing models
Identify and present strategic opportunities based on competitive strategy and positioning
Analyze, calculate and evaluate promotional performance and ROI
Work with the merchandising and E-Commerce teams to optimize pricing and achieve company targets
Grow sales and margin by identifying opportunities and actions that provoke better product performance
Develop and implement Omni pricing strategies to deliver improved sales and earnings for both the stores and E-Commerce
Forecast sales and margin to better understand the impact of seasonal and promotional pricing
Perform and present ad hoc analysis and category/industry trends to leadership
Margin analysis for cost changes
A bachelor's degree or equivalent in business or a related field, economics, mathematics, or analytics
Prefer pricing experience in a corporate retail environment
High Computer Proficiency (Access, Excel, Word) and experience with enterprise / POS systems
Strong interpersonal / communication skills required to work cross functionally with multiple business areas
Exceptional attention to detail and time management skills - ability to manage multiple detailed projects
High proficiency in analytics and problem solving
Must be able to adapt quickly to new computer programs
Excellent verbal, written, and interpersonal skills
Highly desired are familiarity/working knowledge with SQL and Python
Proficient with data and financial modeling and forecasting
Apply now and take advantage of Leslie's competitive salary. Additionally, we offer comprehensive and flexible benefit packages, including healthcare/dental/vision, paid vacation/sick time, paid holidays, 401K with a company match, team member discounts at our retail stores, and most importantly, career advancement opportunities!

Leslie's is committed to developing and fostering a culture of diversity and inclusion within our company and the communities we serve. A key aspect of building a great team is valuing ideas from many viewpoints, which is why we place a priority on identifying and hiring talented individuals from all backgrounds and perspectives.

Gopinath Sundaramurthy, Ph.D
Founder & Head of Data Science @ Ensemble VC
Send InMail
Ensemble VC Data Analyst

The Role:
Ensemble VC is seeking a full-time data analyst to join us this summer. Ensemble VC analyzes and processes data from multiple sources to better understand and invest in the private financial markets. You’ll be working with the data science team to contribute towards developing processes to improve data quality and accuracy which improves the model predictability. This role is ideal for anyone interested in learning a more data-centric approach to decision-making. Title: Data Analyst
Description:
Data Analyst

OMOP Factory, Real World Solutions (RWS) Technology

What problems are we solving?

Currently healthcare professionals and researchers around the world spend days wading through petabytes of health data across multiple formats to discover trends and solutions that could answer some of the post pressing and complex questions in global healthcare.

Our OMOP team have created a solution that enables health professionals to access and convert health data in to a single, accurate, standardised format faster than ever before. This accuracy and speed then enable health professionals to answer those healthcare questions.

We are looking for a data analyst to maintain and support all OMOP data conversion refreshes in Production. You will work with the development team to ensure refreshes are done on-time and according to schedule. You will ensure all backlogs are accurate and reflected in the correct priority. You will be the first line support for all internal and external inquires.

As part of the wider RWS Technology team, you will also have the opportunity to participate in regular innovation weeks, where you can show case your skills and interact with likeminded individuals in the pursuit of innovative software solutions to real world problems.

Key responsibility:

Gather requirements/business rules needed to ETL the source into OMOP CDM.
Troubleshoot problems presented by either an internal or external team
Facilitate and manage all meetings related to the work as well as document the business rules
Resolving any questions/concerns from the team during the refresh
Communicate deliveries of refresh to internal or external teams
Perform first line support duties for both internal and external inquiries
Ensure backlogs are documented properly and in the correct priority order
Participate in scrum agile meetings – sprint planning, retro, backlog grooming, daily stand-ups, sprint demo
Participate in OHDSI Community activities (e.g. working groups, tutorials, symposiums, etc.)
Be able to work with external Clients in a professional manner

Key Requirements:

Excellent communication and writing skills
Ability to facilitate meetings
Presentation and public speaking skills
Ability to gather requirements/business rules
Ability to work with both the business stakeholders and development team
SQL knowledge
Knowledge of ETL process and databases

Nice to Have:

OMOP knowledge a plus
Rabbit in a Hat and White Rabbit a plus
Cloud Computing (e.g. AWS, Azure, Snowflake, etc.)
Big data/Hadoop knowledge
Medical and Pharmaceutical patient level data experience
Experience using Jira and Confluence
Bachelor’s Degree or higher

You’ll fit right in if you:

Are enthusiastic and self-motivated with good decision-making skills.
Speak up! We’re very open here, and we want to hear your opinion and ideas about how we can extend our products and do things better.
Collaborate and work effectively with cross-functional teams in a fast-paced agile environment.

Why join?

Those who join us become part of a recognized global leader still willing to challenge the status quo to improve patient care. In RWS, you will have access to the most cutting-edge technology, the largest data sets, the best analytics tools and, in our opinion, some of the finest minds in the Healthcare industry.

You can drive your career at IQVIA and choose the path that best defines your development and success. With exposure across diverse geographies, capabilities, and vast therapeutic and information and technology areas, you can seek opportunities to change and grow without boundaries.

We thank all applicants for their interest; however only those selected for interview will be contacted.

IQVIA is a strong advocate of diversity and inclusion in the workplace. We believe that a work environment that embraces diversity will give us a competitive advantage in the global marketplace and enhance our success. We believe that an inclusive and respectful workplace culture fosters a sense of belonging among our employees, builds a stronger team, and allows individual employees the opportunity to maximize their personal potential.



At IQVIA, we believe in pushing the boundaries of human science and data science to make the biggest impact possible – to help our customers create a healthier world. The advanced analytics, technology solutions and contract research services we provide to the life sciences industry are made possible by our 67,000+ employees around the world who apply their insight, curiosity and intellectual courage every step of the way. Learn more at jobs.iqvia.com.

IQVIA is an EEO Employer - Minorities/Females/Protected Veterans/Disabled

IQVIA, Inc. provides reasonable accommodations for applicants with disabilities. Applicants who require reasonable accommodation to submit an application for employment or otherwise participate in the application process should contact IQVIA’s Talent Acquisition team at workday_recruiting@iqvia.com to arrange for such an accommodation.

Title: Data Science Analyst - FinLab
Description:
Qualifications
Advanced degree in a STEM-related field, e.g. ops research, statistics, applied math, engineering, business analytics
2 years of related professional experience
Deep understanding of statistical and predictive modeling concepts, machine-learning approaches, clustering and classification techniques, and recommendation and optimization algorithms
Demonstrated proficiency in Python and SQL; additional knowledge of other data mining software (Spark, Scala, etc.) is a plus
Knowledge of the major cloud platforms (AWS, Azure) and associated analytical and data tools (Databricks, EMR, RDS, S3)
Ability to easily understand complex algorithm and logic to process data
Experience working with a large volume of data with ability to solve performance issues
Basic business intuition and clear expertise in analyses; experience describing analytic processes including when and why specific approaches are favored
Excellent communication and presentation skills with an ability to visualize and report insights creatively in variety of formats to various stakeholders

What You'll Do

You'll work with client teams to apply machine learning models and advanced analytics to a large variety of business problems, such as helping a bank build a new product recommendation engine across all of its channels or a retailer determining the best location for its next outlet.

In this role, you will work with a team of McKinsey and client software engineers to deliver the analytics-driven insights through a user friendly interface such as a web-based application or a business intelligence tool (e.g. Power BI). You will work with the client IT team as they set up the necessary infrastructure and processes to support predictive analytics (e.g. ETL from the ERP system to data warehouse/lake). You'll work with McKinsey client teams on analytics methodologies and approaches to address client-specific needs including discussing data collection, architecture, associated costs and trade-offs, and recommendations.

You'll also own an analytics workstream, manage respective tasks and client project team members/experts while building client relationships. Working on projects and exchanging experiences with your colleagues means you will face new intellectual challenges on a daily basis while continuously building your methodological knowledge and skills.

You will keep abreast on the latest technologies and analytics approaches, attending conferences or other events as needed.

Who You'll Work With

You will join our Waltham, Chicago or Dallas office with our FinLab team.

You will work with analytics colleagues, software engineers and architects, McKinsey consultants and clients to carry out complex analyses, build statistical and machine learning models, and develop actionable recommendations for a wide-range of strategic topics in industries such as financial services, real estate, retail and public sector.

McKinsey works with clients in many industries to build custom software solutions that combine deep industry expertise, strategic insights and AI/ML analytics to solve high impact business problems.

REEF’s mission is to connect the world to your block.

Title: Data Analyst
Description:
Description

At PitchBook we work to provide global professionals with comprehensive data on the entire venture capital, private equity and M&A landscape so they can discover and execute opportunities with confidence. We credit our success and rapid growth to our cutting-edge products, customer centered attitude and ability to embrace and drive change.

In just over a decade, PitchBook has reached over 1,300 global employees with offices worldwide, and we’re not slowing down! Consistently recognized as a Best Place to Work, our culture is at the heart of our success and is driven by excellence, inclusion, and fun. At PitchBook we’re committed to fostering an open and collaborative work environment.

Our Institutional Research Group is looking to hire an experienced data analyst to join our Data Analysis & Quantitative Research team. As a valued team member, you’ll work with private markets transaction data to develop meaningful insights into a fascinating industry and power our industry leading private equity, M&A, venture capital, and emerging technology research. In addition, you’ll leverage your analysis skills to interpret client data requests and deliver packaged analytics used by some of the largest private capital investors, investment banks and service providers globally. Our team utilizes technical data analysis skills in conjunction with deep financial and private capital markets industry knowledge to deliver the most accurate and digestible information to our clients.

Team Overview

PitchBook Institutional Research Group is a provider of research services to private market investors, advisors and market participants. The group provides Investment strategy, fund performance, and industry research through a differentiated, framework-driven approach. In addition, the group provides custom research and data analysis support to subscribing clients.

Primary Job Responsibilities
Utilize strong Microsoft Excel and SQL skills in order to provide high-quality data analysis and support to clients, internal stakeholders and select media outlets
Serve as data expert for all use cases that utilize PitchBook’s broad database
Manage and complete time-sensitive custom research requests for subscribing clients
Contribute to and provide data support to broader editorial teams as they develop content for blog posts, data-graphics, and newsletter stories
Opportunity to contribute to research and analysis across the private equity, venture capital and M&A industries
Manage and respond to inquiries from clients, press, internal colleagues and the general public regarding data requests and published research
Support the vision and values of the company through role modeling and encouraging desired behaviors
Participate in various company initiatives and projects as requested
Skills

And Qualifications
Bachelor’s degree with a concentration in Finance, Business Administration or Economics preferred
Strong understanding of financial concepts such as valuation techniques (DCF, comps, etc.), IRRs, asset allocations, etc
1-3 years of experience in financial services role or experience working with large datasets
Strong excel proficiency
Experience in SQL
Experience using Python or other programming languages a plus
Strong interest in M&A and private financial markets
Critical thinker
Detail oriented / analytical mindset
Strong communication skills, both verbal and written
Experience in PitchBook Platform a plus
Proficiency with the MS Office suite including in-depth knowledge of Outlook, Word, and Excel with the ability to pick up new systems and software easily

Title: Data Analyst (Forecasting)
Description:
Data Analysts on the forecasting team are responsible for daily execution of client transaction volume and financial projections. Additionally, this role is responsible for participating in and leading deep dive analyses around program value and pricing, communicating with and delivering analysis to internal and external stakeholders, and ad hoc data analysis requests. We are in search of a driven, self-motivated team-player who will thrive in a constantly changing and time-sensitive environment. This role requires a candidate that is energized by solving complex problems and can win others over by quickly establishing credibility in the analytics space. We’re seeking a team member that will live our core values – a unique, self-motivated, and results-driven individual who acts with integrity and humility.

What You’ll Do

Like most growing companies, the job content of all positions varies daily as everyone pitches in to get the job done. Nonetheless, we try to maintain clarity with respect to employees’ primary responsibilities.
Use SQL, Tableau, Excel, Python, and Alteryx for data visualization, exploration, automation, and creation of stakeholder deliverables
Ensure documentation and stakeholder educational materials are kept up-to-date
Establish standards and templates for stakeholder deliverables
Research launch brand market conditions, competitors, and other external data sources to build assumptions for launch models
Identify opportunities for automation and scalability of data processing and forecasting workflows
Collaborate with sales operations, finance, deal management, pricing, market insights, and clinical teams to fine tune assumptions and adjustments on an individual brand basis
Perform QA on our automated processes and investigate anomalies
About You

The ideal candidate will be a natural collaborator with strong analytical skills and an innate drive to innovate.
Bachelor's degree in a quantitative discipline
3+ years' experience in an analytics role
1+ years working with time series forecasting methods and tools
Strong interest in and aptitude for data analytics
Strong critical thinking and problem solving skills
Desire to constantly learn and teach others what you know
Experience with SQL for advanced querying and data transformation
Experience with a data visualization tool such as Tableau or Power BI
Some Python or R experience
Alteryx experience a plus
About Us

CoverMyMeds, part of McKesson’s Prescription Technology Solutions, is a fast-growing healthcare technology company. Our mission: Help patients get the medications they need to live healthy lives. Our solutions seamlessly connect the health care network to improve medication access, increasing speed to therapy and reducing prescription abandonment for patients like you and me.

We hire ambitious people and make it a priority to invest in them by providing opportunities to grow their careers and connections within the community. On-site culinary team, flexible hours and paid benefits? Yeah, we have those too. But don’t take our word for it. We’ve been recognized as a “Best Place to Work” by Glassdoor, a “Best Company to Work For” by FORTUNE, and our employees have great things to say, too.

CoverMyMeds is an equal opportunity and affirmative action employer. We embrace diversity and are committed to creating an inclusive environment for all employees. Qualified applicants will be considered for employment without regard to race, religion, gender, gender identity, sexual orientation, national origin, age, disability or veteran status.

Title: Data Analyst
Description:
ABOUT CCS FUNDRAISING
CCS Fundraising is an international strategic fundraising firm that partners with nonprofits for transformational change. For seven decades, CCS has empowered many of the world’s greatest organizations across sectors to advance some of the most important causes in history. We plan, manage, and implement programs and initiatives that achieve fundraising goals and mission impact.
 CCS provides tailored support to more than 400 nonprofit organizations annually. With over 300 professionals and 14 offices throughout the United States and Europe, we have the capacity to help local and international organizations achieve outstanding results.
 Our services include:
Campaign Management
Strategy, Evaluation & Planning
Interim Development Management
Learning & Leadership Development
Data Analytics
 A CAREER AT CCS
Our people are our greatest strength. The collective sum of the individual experiences, backgrounds, knowledge, and talent that our employees invest in their work represents a significant part of not only our culture, but our reputation of excellence.
 Whether it’s in one of our regional offices or on the ground with our clients, you will have direct access to leaders in the field, expanding your opportunities to learn and build your network for future success. We invest in the training, tools, and support necessary for growth throughout your career and encourage peer collaboration in a lively and engaging environment.
 Our staff report that the best aspects of working for CCS are the relationships with colleagues, leading nonprofits, and philanthropists; the performance-based career paths; and the diversity of projects.
 THE CCS ANALYTICS PRACTICE
The CCS Analytics Practice is a passionate group of high-performing staff that provide specialized data analytics and predictive modeling services to clients supported by project teams throughout the firm.
 The Data Analytics Practice at CCS is experiencing rapid growth, resulting in a need to expand the team. We are looking for individuals with skills and insights that will allow us to provide high-quality data analytics services to our clients and develop new innovative services. These new members will bring passion, teamwork, and creativity to the job every day.  
 Our process is a collaborative, team-focused approach, which means that you will have the opportunity to work on multiple aspects of a client project. On any given day you may find yourself assisting with client onboarding, vetting and validating data sets, creating pivot tables and other supporting analyses, crafting presentation materials, or participating in the presentation of our work to the client. We encourage all members of the team to develop these skills to participate in each of these steps.
 Our main objective is to identify opportunity in a client’s constituent database. We offer the following services to meet that objective.
 Predictive Modeling:
Uses statistical techniques to score a client’s constituents based on data provided from the client’s internal database. By combining wealth capacity data with the affinity scores generated by the predictive models we can:
Identify new compelling major gift prospects.
Evaluate the currently managed prospects to find new, untapped opportunity.
 RFM Analysis:
Scores a client's donors to summarize best givers based on a donor’s recency, frequency and magnitude of giving. Wealth screening data is combined with the RFM scores to prioritize a client's best prospects.
 Year-over-Year Trend Analysis and Benchmarking:
Compares fundraising performance over multiple time periods, sources and gift funds to help identify trend and anomalies that may shed light of future fundraising performance.
 WE ARE LOOKING FOR A DEDICATED PROFESSIONAL THAT HAS:
At least three years of professional experience
The ability to communicate clearly, concisely, and logically both verbally and in writing. 
Comfort articulating strategies with a variety of audiences
Strong analytical and problem-solving skills with a passion to dig into large data sets and provide insights that are relevant to our clients
Data visualization skills and can use those skills to tell a compelling story
Meaningful experience with Microsoft Excel, PowerPoint, and data visualization software, such as PowerBI or Tableau
Adaptability to manage changing workflows, new situations, and varied personalities
The proficiency to review and proofread presentations and other client reports
 Other helpful skills include:
Experience with the predictive modeling process.
Familiarity with fundraising data.
Working knowledge of scripting tools such as Python
 CCS offers a competitive benefits package and is an Affirmative Action Equal Opportunity Employer

Title: Intelligence and Data Analyst 1
Description:
Job Introduction

Hiring Now!

The world's leading private security organization, G4S, has an immediate job opportunity for an Intelligence and Data Analyst 1 . The Intelligence and Data Analyst 1 is responsible for conducting comprehensive all-source collection, analysis, and dissemination of intelligence products concerning the global threat environment, with a focus on the Asia Pacific region. This position is responsible for gathering and analyzing information from a variety of sources, particularly open sources, to determine significance and promptly inform senior management to create decision advantage, while strictly adhering to established analytic standards of being objective, accurate, timely, relevant and actionable. Intelligence products will be produced for the Director of Intelligence, Chief Security Officer and various Business units. This position will further be required to produce due diligence reports, and conduct data analytics (for example, on aggregating survey inputs.)

G4S is a security provider for the United States government, fortune 500 companies, nuclear power plants, oil and gas companies, airport, ports, banks, hospitals, factories, warehouses, commercial facilities, residential communities and much more.

As a full time employee of G4S, you will be entitled to the following benefits:
Major Medical, Dental and Vision

401K
Opportunities for additional training to aid in your professional development

As an employee you will also be able to participate in the Promote Me! Community. Promote Me! is available to interested current employees as a way to express interest in further advancement, as well as gain information and encourage professional development.

Further, as a current employee you will be eligible to participate in large group rates for the following benefits:
Critical Illness
Accident Insurance
Whole Life Insurance
Individual Short-Term Disability
Pre-Paid Legal Services
Identity Theft Services

In addition, G4S provides benefits that are automatically available to all employees, whether you enroll in a G4S insurance plan or not. And with no premiums to pay!

G4S offers job security, excellent pay and benefits, and career opportunities. We offer entry level careers, management careers, sales careers and executive careers across the United States and internationally.

Role Responsibility

Specific Duties and Essential Functions
Conduct all-source collection and research, analyze, evaluate, and integrate data from multiple sources, identify intelligence gaps, and specify collection requirements to produce assessments and recommendations
Prepare analyses, assessments, verbal briefs or other products by applying expert judgment and specialized experience in interpreting information and making decisions
Extract essential information and analysis from a variety of sources and synthesize the information into actionable reports
Support due diligence investigations
Conduct data analysis, for example aggregating survey inputs, and reviewing metrics
Prepare and/or review all submitted analytical and investigative reports to ensure accuracy, research, investigative sufficiency, and professional quality; edit and correct, as necessary and disseminate to decision makers
Prepare graphs, charts (link analysis, event flow analysis, activity charting), tables and other illustrative devices for visual presentation of data
Conduct background research on groups, individuals, events, and/or incidents that may have a negative impact on client business


The Ideal Candidate

Education, Licenses and Certifications Required
Must possess a Bachelor’s Degree in an intelligence related field of study, preferably intelligence studies, national security, political science, international affairs, criminology, statistical analysis or other relevant four-year degree from a national accredited program


Type And Length Of Specific Experience Required
Must be able to produce due-diligence reports
Must possess at least one (1) year of previous work experience in national security, military intelligence, criminal intelligence analysis, corporate intelligence analysis, or data analytics involving the principles, concepts, and methodologies of all-source intelligence analysis to research, evaluate, and integrate all-source data in the preparation and presentation of intelligence analytical products
Must be able to demonstrate each of the following:
Ability to develop metrics, perform critical analysis, identify threats and develop leadership decision support content
Analytical expertise necessary to accurately draw conclusions by synthesizing raw data and information from multiple unrelated sources into a finished comprehensive product.
Deep understanding of current global threat dynamics and trends, including—but not limited to—violent extremism, terrorism, geopolitical risk, cyber threats, and criminal activity
A proven ability to independently and efficiently handle multiple time sensitive projects, rapid change and ambiguity while maintaining the highest analytical standards and direct contact with intelligence consumers, including making challenging judgment calls in the absence of senior leaders.
Experience learning and quickly becoming proficient maintaining databases and utilizing software applications, such as: Analyst's Notebook or other intelligence analysis and data collection tools, case management tools, social media analysis tools, and geographic information systems, as well as the Microsoft Office suite
Analytical expertise necessary to accurately draw conclusions by synthesizing raw data and information from multiple unrelated sources into a finished comprehensive product

While not required, the following attributes would be preferred for this position:
Experience conducting data analytics is highly desired
Foreign language fluency is beneficial, especially Portuguese, Indonesian, Mandarin, Hindi, Malay, and/or Japanese
Familiarity with the Asia Pacific region is beneficial
A Master’s Degree in national security, military intelligence, criminal intelligence analysis, corporate intelligence analysis, or data analytics related studies


Skills Required
Proficient computer skills including Microsoft Office and/or Google Applications
Effective oral and written communication skills
Active listening skills
Ability to assess and evaluate situations effectively

Attention to detail


Other

Able to produce high-quality detailed documentation to internal and external parties while managing sensitive or confidential information
A proven ability to independently and efficiently handle multiple time-sensitive projects, rapid change and ambiguity while maintaining the highest analytical standards and direct contact with intelligence consumers, including making challenging judgment calls in the absence of senior leaders

  We are currently recruiting for the Data Analyst to join the Benchmade Knife Company team.   The Data Analyst will create both standard and custom reports, conduct quantitative and qualitative company analysis. They will also track the performance relative to goals, benchmarks, and other key criteria. They will be responsible for using data based on sales, leads, and customer information to gain insight into customer behavior and promotion/campaign performance. The Analyst will work with the Sales and Marketing team and other internal and external groups to obtain the necessary data and perform the required analysis. They provide advice to marketing departments, sales teams, and executives to develop sales targets, assess strategies to boost revenue. This is a data-driven role that requires a balance of market analysis and industry expertise. The Data Analyst will work closely with sales and marketing teams while providing advice and guidance to company decision-makers.

Understands the team's strategy and goals and anticipates the reporting needs of the team.

Serves as a resource to others to analyze statistics, brainstorm ideas based on results about why certain sales and marketing activities performed well or not.
Develops easy-to-understand dashboards, spreadsheets, and presentations that the sales and marketing team can show internal and external stakeholders. Communicates progress with projects often and in a clear, concise writing style.
Proactively monitors and analyzes trends in performance metrics to identify which activities/promotions/campaigns are working best and why and what tactics can be improved upon. Presents recommendations for improvement on a monthly, quarterly, and annual basis.
Identify, Create and maintain data visualization dashboards
Participates in special projects and performs other duties as required.
Be highly analytical with a proven ability to turn data into compelling insight.
Ensure data quality - Help manage processes to build new and improve existing data pipelines. Help drive, guide, and inspect the quality of team deliverables.
Support data inquiries. Analyze data and identify trends. Draw conclusions, present insights, and tell compelling stories. Be a self-starter - work independently with minimal direction or oversight.

7-8 years of direct experience with analytics, reporting, data mining, advanced analytical modeling, and data visualization.
Statistics experience/experience in descriptive, exploratory, inferential, predictive, and causal analysis.
Knowledge of BI tools (Tableau, Alteryx).
Salesforce experience is a plus
Experience working directly with sales and marketing teams to gather and analyze data.
Demonstrated proficiency in statistics and data with an understanding of their financial and operational impacts.
Experienced with other software packages, including Windows, Microsoft Office, advanced excel, and ERP systems.
This position requires strong analytical, organizational, decision making, and presentation skills.

Title: Data Science - Analyst 3
Industry: Marketing & Advertising Information Technology & Services Internet
Description:
Looking for a company that inspires passion, courage and imagination, where you can be part of the team shaping the future of global commerce? Want to shape how millions of people buy, sell, connect, and share around the world? If you're interested in joining a purpose-driven community that is dedicated to creating an ambitious and inclusive environment, join eBay - a company you can be proud to be a part of.

Advertising is one of the fastest growing areas in ebay which in some ways, will define the future of ebay. Digital advertising as an industry is growing rapidly, and the landscape is shifting as ecommerce advertisers are finding better value with ecommerce companies like ebay. As they shift budget from the duopoly of google and facebook, it creates a huge opportunity for ebay. Advertising is also amplifying ebay’s ecommerce by providing a tool for our sellers to move inventory and for buyers, by surfacing high quality items.

We are looking to hire a Data Scientist to partner closely with the eBay Advertising product team. As a critical member of the Advertising Product Insights team, you will influence the Ads Product roadmap with your insights and thought leadership. You will identify opportunities to drive dynamic change in the customer experience that results in significant business growth.

We mine the largest datasets in the world of e-Commerce and use analytic and big data techniques to extract impactful insights. We achieve this by partnering closely with the advertising product and engineering teams, and find opportunities to craft the product roadmaps.

To Be Successful In This Role
5+ years of experience in analytics/data science
Master’s degree in Statistics, Mathematics, Computer Science, Data Science, Economics, Business Administration or Business Analytics.
Balance of critical thinking and hands-on analyses using tools & packages such as SQL, R, Python, Tableau etc.
Excellent technical skills to turn big data in Hadoop into impactful insights.
Ability to see the big picture and connect the dots to evaluate how the insights impact eBay’s ecosystem.
Effective project management skills
Proactive collaboration and effective communication skills
Additionally, The Following Background And Experience Is Preferred
Consistent track record of turning insights into product growth opportunities in prior roles with growing scope and responsibilities

Title: Data Analyst - Information Management
Industry: Hospital & Health Care
Description:
Job ID: 1080583_RR00048244

NYU Grossman School of Medicine is one of the nation's top-ranked medical schools. For 175 years, NYU Grossman School of Medicine has trained thousands of physicians and scientists who have helped to shape the course of medical history and enrich the lives of countless people. An integral part of NYU Langone Health, the Grossman School of Medicine at its core is committed to improving the human condition through medical education, scientific research, and direct patient care. For more information, go to med.nyu.edu, and interact with us on LinkedIn, Glassdoor, Indeed, Facebook, Twitter and Instagram.

Position Summary

We have an exciting opportunity to join our team as a Data Analyst - Information Management.

We are seeking a qualified Data Analyst to provide support for data management and analyses across the Rapid RCT portfolio of projects and other medical center efforts. This Data Analyst will be joining NYU Langone Health's Data Core, an innovative organization that utilizes state-of-the-art technologies and informatics products to meet the clinical research needs of a prestigious institution. Members of Data Core work closely with clinicians, researchers, and administrators to build queries and perform analytics on clinical data. Operationally, the data analyst will focus on supporting the Center for Healthcare Innovation and Delivery Science (CHIDS). The particular Data Analyst will work directly with, and report to, Dr. Leora Horwitz, the Director of the Division of Healthcare Delivery Science and the Center for Healthcare Innovations and Delivery Science, as well as the Rapid RCT Lab.

Job Responsibilities
Planning, designing, and implementing statistical analyses. Work autonomously and comfortably in an academic medical center environment.
Work with clinical, administrative and operational data, and be responsible for analyzing and presenting data; performing data analysis in support of ad-hoc and standing customer requests;
Responsible for managing and improving existing databases; developing programs, methodologies, and files for analyzing and presenting data;
Play an active role in providing clinical data for operational improvements.
Performs additional duties as assigned.

Minimum Qualifications

To qualify you must have a Bachelors Degree and 3 years or more years of relevant experience.
Familiarity with healthcare data (EHR, clinical, claims, etc.) is essential.
Extensive database query/development experience, particularly on the Oracle PL-SQL and ETL side. Excellent communication skills are essential.

Preferred Qualifications

Familiarity with Informatica, Business Objects or another Business Intelligence/Reporting tool, statistical programming software (e.g. R, SAS, SPSS), and Microsoft Office is also preferred.
Advanced training (MPH, biomedical informatics) is a plus.

Qualified candidates must be able to effectively communicate with all levels of the organization.

NYU Grossman School of Medicine provides its staff with far more than just a place to work. Rather, we are an institution you can be proud of, an institution where you'll feel good about devoting your time and your talents.

NYU Grossman School of Medicine is an equal opportunity and affirmative action employer committed to diversity and inclusion in all aspects of recruiting and employment. Title: Data Engineering Analyst (Office of Technology and Data Science)
Description:
Who we are:

At the Urban Institute, we believe in the power of evidence to improve lives and strengthen communities.  Our employees are empowered to influence policy, open minds, shape decisions, and offer solutions.  We encourage intellectual honesty, innovation, diversity, and mutual respect, and our analysis elevates debate, wherever it takes place.

How you’ll contribute:

The Data Science, Data Engineering, and Research Technology Teams are made up of polyglot programmers who use tools such as R, Python, C, C++, Fortran, SAS, STATA, and cloud computing technologies to translate public policy and proposals into algorithms and code.
The teams support research and develop tools, data, and computing platforms in languages such as R and Python and in cloud environments such as AWS. These technologies and platforms often include natural language processing, big data, web scraping, machine learning, and cloud computing technology.

Responsibilities include:

Maintain, modify, and develop existing code-bases and new tools, including APIs, data pipelines, and processes
Analyze and collect data using techniques and platforms such as natural language processing, big data, machine learning, and cloud computing technology
Analyze data in R or Python programming languages
Work with both Technical and research staff
Apply and implement research principles and goals into code
Effectively communicate results back to research staff
Debug and solve programming problems
Take the initiative to suggest improvements or innovations of methods or processes

What you’ll bring:

The successful candidate will have:

A Bachelor’s degree or equivalent experience, with a concentration in Computer Science, Data Science, Mathematics, Economics, Statistics, or related fields
Up to 2 years of experience in a professional or academic environment with R or Python programming languages (a short programming exercise is required as part of the process)
Experience with version control such as git and GitHub
Some exposure to cloud architectures and technologies
Willingness to learn and adapt to changes in work assignments, deadlines, and team environment
Ability to communicate clearly to both technical and non-technical staff
Interest in economic and social policy
Proven ability to consistently manage and prioritize multiple tasks, projects, and relationships
Strong organizational skills, attention to detail, and the ability to prioritize
Ability to communicate respectfully with individuals of differing backgrounds and experience

What you’ll experience:

Working in the Nation’s Capital, the epicenter of public policy among a network of policy experts, you can expect to have an impact on policy areas you care about and work with great colleagues who are smart, mission-driven, and collaborative.  You will blend academic rigor with on-the-ground collaboration, be encouraged and supported to fulfill your potential through meaningful work that matters and, enjoy a welcoming workplace free from harassment, discrimination, and intolerance.
In addition, we offer a comprehensive benefits package that includes: medical, dental, disability, and life insurance coverage.  Competitive paid time off allowance, and eligibility to participate in a generous retirement savings plan plus elect a pretax benefit for commuting expenses.
The Urban Institute is committed to Equal Employment Opportunity without regard for race, ethnicity, gender, protected veteran status, disability, sexual orientation, gender identity or any other protected status under applicable law.
The Urban Institute is an Equal Opportunity/Affirmative Action Employer Minorities/Women/Disabilities/Veterans.

Title: Data Analyst - Data Services
Description:
WHO ARE WE?
Live Nation Entertainment is the world’s leading live entertainment company, comprised of global market leaders: Ticketmaster, Live Nation Concerts, and Live Nation Media & Sponsorship. Ticketmaster is the global leader in event ticketing with over 500 million tickets sold annually and more than 12,000 clients worldwide. Live Nation Concerts is the largest provider of live entertainment in the world promoting more than 40,000 shows and 100+ festivals annually for nearly 4,000 artists in over 40 countries. These businesses allow Live Nation Media & Sponsorship to create strategic music marketing programs that connect over 1,000 brands with the 98 million fans that attend Live Nation Entertainment events each year.
