Title: Data Analyst
Description:
About Centria Healthcare

Founded in 2009 and headquartered in Farmington Hills, Michigan, Centria Healthcare is a leading provider of home-based catastrophic injury and rehabilitation care, private duty nursing, and supportive living services. Centria Healthcare Autism Services is the largest provider of Applied Behavior Analysis (ABA) for children with Autism Spectrum Disorder (ASD) across the state of Michigan, with services in other states.

Position Overview

The HR Analyst is responsible for partnering with leaders and human resources partners to help drive employee engagement and retention through reporting and analytics. The HR Analyst will use industry best practices and innovations to support the engagement efforts across the organization.

Responsibilities

The ideal candidate must be able to perform the following essential job functions with or without reasonable accommodations:
Responsible for supporting the execution of the employee engagement strategy through qualitative and quantitative research and reporting
Analyzes and recognizes patterns in employee data to help leaders identify risks and opportunities
Identify trends and patterns through the analysis of survey data
Provide data-driven recommendations to enhance employee engagement across Centria
Identify issues and trends within written feedback/comments by reviewing and categorizing feedback by topic, sentiment, etc.
Constructs concise presentations and/or reporting, including tracking of employee engagement progress
Collaborate with the human resources and Engagement teams on the interpretation and analysis of the engagement survey data to improve engagement and performance
Research industry standards relative to healthcare and conduct/report on benchmarks, best practices, and trends in employee engagement for remote and internal team members
Ensure the ongoing maintenance of engagement surveying system
Work to enhance and create opportunities based upon analytics to continuously improve employee satisfaction and engagement
Build relationships and collaborate across the teams to provide high levels of internal customer service
Maintain a high level of confidentiality related to engagement reports, employee feedback, management performance and action plans
Commencement and/or commencement related activities may be required
Learn new software and assist with implementation of a new survey software system
Create and track KPIs relative to human capital
Automate current analytic processes using forms and/or macro’s to efficiently process data
Assist with ad hoc analysis requests
Other duties as assigned
Required Qualifications

, Skills, And Knowledge
Bachelor’s degree in Human Resources or related field
At least one year of experience in an analyst capacity, human resources or related field
Experience with qualitative and quantitative data analysis
Ability to extract, organize and analyze data sets
Strong research and analytical skills and the ability to visually present data in a consumable format
Expert level Excel skills and strong knowledge of Word and PowerPoint
Knowledge of and experience with Engagement software system(s)
Ability to utilize Power BI for data visualization and dashboards
Understanding of statistical modeling (e.g., Pearson correlation coefficient)
Experience with predictive analytics relative to human capital
Working Conditions

Centria’s office hours are Monday through Friday from 8:30am-6:00pm. Additional time may be required to complete above work or meet company objectives.

Physical Requirements

While performing the duties of this job, physical requirements such as bending, reaching and lifting of up to 50 pounds may be required. This role will require sitting a majority of the day as well as walking as standing when needed. This role will require close visual activity on multiple computer screens or monitors and the ability to analyze data and figures on a screen.

Title: Data Analyst, Finance
Industry: Financial Services
Description:
Job Description
We build financial technology to help more business owners succeed. Our goal is to revolutionize the business economy by evolving how funding flows. We’re looking for a talented Data Analyst to join our exceptional team, help us continue our rapid growth, and create a better way forward for our customers. In this position on our finance team, you will have an opportunity to help develop and scale the finance function. 
This individual will build and own a vast array of financial reporting and data analysis in order to help support various finance and accounting functions, including helping to drive strategy, execution and management of capital markets transactions as Fundbox continues to grow and scale.

In this role, you will
Design, build, automate & own robust and scalable reporting for both internal and external partners
Manage reporting and accuracy of key financial data metrics used for operational decision-making, financial and capital markets reporting and analysis
Identify growth opportunities and work with business partners to execute 
Partner with team leads to define key metrics and build and/or automate reporting to monitor and analyze performance amongst other key metrics

You should have
5+ years in data analytics, data science, consulting, banking, or other relevant experience
Senior to expert level Proficiency in SQL, R and Python experience a plus
Exposure to asset-backed finance/capital markets analysis and reporting a plus
Experience with Tableau or other data visualization tools 
Advanced skills in Excel well as PowerPoint, including the ability to build dynamic financial models and presentations
Ability to forge strong relationships and partnerships with other departments at all levels of the organization
Strong analytical, problem solving and critical thinking skills

About Fundbox
Our goal is to power the small business economy. Our story began when our co-founder’s mother encountered cash flow problems when she tried to grow her small business. The challenges she faced inspired her son to solve the most important problems for business owners and help them access capital and financial tools. Today, we combine cutting-edge machine learning and data science technologies with outstanding design and top-notch user support that earns rave reviews from our thousands of happy customers. Fundbox has raised over $300 million in capital from leading Silicon Valley investors such as Khosla Ventures, General Catalyst Partners, Spark Capital, Allianz, and MUFG. Fundbox has offices in downtown San Francisco, Dallas and Tel Aviv, Israel.

San Francisco Office
Our San Francisco headquarters are located in the heart of downtown, just a few minutes walk from public transportation, great restaurants, and everything the city offers. Our space is open and modern, with plenty of natural light, a fully-stocked kitchen, free drinks and snacks, and gourmet lunches delivered daily. We offer a choice of comprehensive health, dental, and vision plans, 401k, Fundbox Fit fitness reimbursement plan, and commuter benefits. We take our jobs seriously, but we also know how to have fun, with sponsored social activities and plenty of opportunities to celebrate our achievements.

Diversity and Inclusion at Fundbox
We’re proud to be an equal opportunity workplace as we know that diverse teams produce the best work. We’re committed to building a culture of innovation and inclusion across gender, race, age, sexual orientation, religion, disability, and identity. Here at Fundbox, we strive to uphold a system of values we call MOSAIC: Mission, Ownership, Speed, Achva (a Hebrew term meaning to help one another), Innovation, and Clarity. Embracing our diverse backgrounds and abilities allows us to harness our creativity and achieve more, together.

Title: Data Analyst
Description:

Position Description

The Data Management Analyst is an integral role in documenting lineage, dataflows, and metadata of the company's enterprise information, processes, and assets. The candidate will work with stakeholders and subject matter experts, to develop, optimize and oversee conceptual and logical data systems, data stores, and.

• Hands-on experience and technical skills in designing and implementing enterprise level solutions.

Title: Data Analyst
Description:
How will this role have an impact?

This position will be responsible for fulfilling our internal departments, as well as external clients’ needs from an analytics perspective and develop reporting to satisfy those needs. The candidate filling this position needs to have advanced technical abilities in order to mine data from multiple sources (SQL server and flat files) and transform that data into meaningful insight that will be consumed by individuals from various backgrounds.The candidate will work with the Technology team, Client Services, and other business groups to gather information and understand any request. In addition, this position is responsible for supporting, identifying new solutions focusing on optimizing our current process to deliver data and insights to clients.

This role will also participate in the development of analytics strategy in collaboration with Client Services team.

This role will report to our Manager, Decision Analytics.

What will you do?
Extending company’s data with third party sources of information when needed
Enhancing data analysis procedures to include information that is relevant for building analytic systems
Doing ad-hoc analysis and presenting results in a clear manner
Partner with client, operations and other teams to drive understanding of our product offerings and services through data analysis.
Provide data, reports and insights that could be easily understood by non-technical individuals.
Work closely with Client Services to gather requirements and to develop solutions to fulfil clients’ requests.
Proactively monitor, identify, and help our IT partners resolve system production issues.
Implementing automated solutions for recurring ad hoc data extraction.


We Are Looking For Someone With
Bachelor’s degree in Math, Statistics or Computer Science or related field or equivalent work experience
Master’s degree in Mathematics or technology preferred
5+ years professional experience (quantitative disciplines such as math, statistics, computer science, information systems preferred)
Must have healthcare industry experience.
Experience with SQL Server, Reporting, and Data Cubes
Experience with Replication and ETL
Experience in statistical and data analysis (e.g. significance testing, regression modelling, factor analysis, etc.) or experience in machine learning, predictive or descriptive analytics, preferred
Experience using business intelligence tools (e.g. Tableau) and data frameworks
Demonstrated ability to develop and present business cases
Ability to rapidly assess, analyze and resolve complicated issues, and distill that complexity into simple and concise communication


About Us

Signify Health is helping build the healthcare system we all want to experience by transforming the home into the healthcare hub. We coordinate care holistically across individuals’ clinical, social, and behavioral needs so they can enjoy more healthy days at home. By building strong connections to primary care providers and community resources, we’re able to close critical care and social gaps, as well as manage risk for individuals who need help the most. This leads to better outcomes and a better experience for everyone involved.

Our high-performance networks are powered by more than 9,000 mobile doctors and nurses covering every county in the U.S., 3,500 healthcare providers and facilities in value-based arrangements, and hundreds of community-based organizations. Signify’s intelligent technology and decision-support services enable these resources to radically simplify care coordination for more than 1.5 million individuals each year while helping payers and providers more effectively implement value-based care programs.

To learn more about how we’re driving outcomes and making healthcare work better, please visit us at www.signifyhealth.com.

Title: Data Quality Analyst(Talend)

Job Description:
The Data Quality Analyst/Data Quality Analyst Lead is accountable for the design and operational execution of the Enterprise Information Service Data Quality framework, as well as well as coordination across all technical resources throughout the lifecycle of information investigation and data management. 
Secondary responsibilities include creation and maintenance of various types of documents, quality assurance testing support and assisting in delivery activities.

 Leads data quality analysis to support Enterprise Information ServicesData Warehouse projects. Work closely with Business Analysts, Data Analysts/Scientists, Development, and Product Owners to ensure data housed in multiple source systems is valid and accurate.

Regularly review and interprets QA results and findings with limited support from senior leadership. 
Uses out-of-the-box ingenuity in applying analytical techniques and organizational skills to identifying and evaluating alternatives and to developing recommended approaches to resolving quality assurance issues and problems. 

Qualifications:
Bachelor’s degree with at least five to eight years related experience or equivalent combination of education and experience (systems consulting experience desired). 
At least three years’ experience in large scale system implementation efforts following a standard software development lifecycle approach (scrum desired). Experience with business and technical requirements analysis, data modeling/mapping, and quality assurance frameworks. Strong oral and written communications skills.
 Ability to create systematic and manual data quality operations procedures in both technical and user-friendly language.

About The Department

The Division of Human Resources encompasses the functional areas of employment, classification and compensation, benefits, employee relations, training and organizational development, human resources information management, employee onboarding, and continuous improvement. These services are directed, managed, and provided by the division for over 4000 SHRA/staff employees, approximately 2000 EHRA professional and administrative employees, and 1800 faculty. The Division provides leadership to the university administration, managers, and employees by being a progressive and innovative provider of human resources services.

Human Resource Information Management and Analytics (HRIM) provides a broad range of university support regarding the HR System including; upgrades, Job Action Request (JAR), time & labor, payable compensation, longevity, prior state service, job data and record management. HRIM works directly with college divisional HR representatives when processing and investigating HR System transactions.

The HR System is a web-based PeopleSoft application accessible from the MYPACK Portal with a valid unity ID and password. The application supports the information needs of Human Resources (HR), Payroll, Employee Services, Benefits, and Management functions within the university. It merges resource management activities into standardized categories, folders, sub folders, and topics. The linkage of its payroll and human resource activities in the HR System makes the software application both rigid and flexible for processing personnel actions.

HRIM also maintains personnel records for EHRA and SHRA employees.

Essential

Job Duties

The primary function of this IT Business Intelligence/Data Analyst position is the development and management of complex data analytics and metrics utilizing Human Resources data sources. This position will be responsible for the development, analysis and communication of data-driven insights that can be leveraged by University Senior Leadership and HR Leadership to make business-driven decisions. The incumbent in this role will possess the practical experience to execute and advise on technical and business requirements, and liaise with other technical personnel to design and build datasets needed to accomplish HR strategic and business goals. It will be essential that the incumbent have knowledgeable of data mining, statistical analysis and/or data analytic techniques.

Collaborate in the ongoing development and maintenance of the University HR data strategy, and works in collaboration with the HRIM Director in the development and maintenance of data governance protocols including field definitions, access rights and storage mechanisms.

Identify opportunities to leverage data effectively, and optimize the capabilities for data collection, information management, data quality, and data analytics strategy, standards, and metrics.
Identify process improvement opportunities that will improve data quality and data storytelling across the University HR as well as College and Division HR offices.

Title: Data Analyst, Strategy and Analytics
Description:
In February 2021, Constant Contact's former parent company, Endurance Group, was acquired by Clearlake Capital and Siris Capital. As part of this acquisition, Constant Contact was spun off to operate as a stand-alone business and Endurance has been dissolved.

We couldn't be more excited to continue the focus on building simple, yet powerful tools that help small businesses achieve their goals with our new partnership.

Constant Contact, Inc. helps small businesses and nonprofits connect with their customers, clients, and members. Constant Contact® champions the needs of small organizations and provides an easy, affordable way to build successful, lasting customer relationships. Our customers get real results through email newsletters, surveys, events, Facebook promotions, online listings, and more. We're looking to expand our Analytics team in our Waltham office.

Do you thrive in a fast-paced, analytical environment where innovation, excellence and creating actionable insight are not just catch-phrases but steeped in the company’s culture? We seek an Analyst with strong analytical and problem solving skills that has business curiosity. Serving an array of business stakeholders across the organization, the Analyst will conduct and analyze data on customer behavior, profiles, and product engagement. As a part of cross-functional teams (e.g Product Owners, Marketers, Finance) you will be responsible for innovating the customer experience throughout the customer lifecycle and conduct analyses to uncover customer insights. The Analytics team is on a journey to develop a deep understanding of our customers across all aspects of their lifecycle leveraging internal and 3rd party data. The group also focuses on internal performance optimization.

What You’ll Do
Collaborate with Marketing, Product Management, Finance, UX, and other internal stakeholders to identify opportunities for analysis and optimization of product experience and acquire and retain valuable customers
Provide insights into product behavior and engagement to the rest of the business
Partner closely with the data warehouse team to understand data availability and the flow of data through various systems
Conduct analysis of prospects and customers for product design, go-to-market strategies and retention engagement efforts
Develop data inquiries, and conduct data exploration and data mining to determine program effectiveness and predict future performance
Partner closely with business stakeholders to ensure insights are leading to action and measuring the business impact
Who You Are
Bachelor’s degree (preferably in a quantitative field such as business, math, statistics or computer science)
3 to 5 years of experience conducting analytical analyses in a business setting and telling stories with data
Must be results driven, and take appropriate steps to achieve goals while taking ownership of situations as needed
Must have excellent organizational skills, strong attention to detail and ability to effectively manage projects supporting multiple business partners
Resourceful and a motivated problem solver. You enjoy and have demonstrated ability tackling complex problems, drawing inferences from data, and using your analysis skills and business acumen to identify solutions.
Strong experience with SQL and Tableau
Strong communication skills. An ability to talk both to the technical teams responsible for the data and comfortable explaining data and conclusions to non-technical teams
Experience manipulating and cleansing data in Python and/or R a plus
Prior experience with Adobe Analytics or Google Analytics a plus
Why You’ll Love Us
In this era of COVID-19, we believe in putting our employees first and keeping them safe. We were one of the first technology companies to make significant changes to our office environments and team interactions, including mandatory working from home and safety procedures to enter our office space. We are committed to not require any face-to-face interaction for our employees until the data shows it is entirely safe for our teams. We have made the decision to stay remote until June 2021.
We celebrate one another’s differences. Although we're proud of our culture of diversity and inclusion, we're working hard to strengthen and improve this culture. We have programs in place that bring us together on important issues and provide educational opportunities for all employees.
Join the experts. If you're passionate about supporting businesses of all sizes, you won’t find a better spot to share your talent. We’re dedicated to improving the quality of our product from a customer standpoint, and have a true desire to “help the little guy/gals”.
You’ll have opportunities to advance. We’re fans of helping our employees learn different aspects of the business, be challenged with new tasks, be mentored and grow.
We’ve got you covered. We are a family! From medical to life insurance, education sponsorships to interest-free loans, Flexi-leave to casual dress code - we've got your back!

Title: Data Analyst
Description:
About Well Health

Our Mission: Make healthcare the gold standard in customer service.

What We Deliver: WELLTM Health is a SaaS digital health leader in patient communications and the 2021 Best in KLAS winner in Patient Outreach. WELL Health's intelligent communications hub is the only two-way digital health solution engaging patients throughout their entire care experience. WELL Health enables conversations between patients and their providers through secure, multilingual messaging in the patient's preferred communications channel: texting, email, telephone, and live chat. By unifying and automating disjointed communications, WELL Health helps healthcare organizations drive more patient visits, build exceptional patient loyalty, and reduce staffing costs, frustration and turnover.

Our Impact: WELL Health helps 200k+ healthcare providers facilitate more than 1 billion messages for 30+ million patients annually.

Our award-winning culture: In 2021, WELL Health was named No.10 on the Forbes list of America's Best Startup Employers and was also recognized as one of the Best Midsize Companies to Work for in Los Angeles by Built In LA. In 2020, WELL Health was named among the Best Places to Work by Modern Healthcare and ranked #170 on the Inc. 5000 list of fastest growing private companies.

Summary

WELL is seeking an experienced Data Analyst to join our growing organization. You will work alongside other talented Data Engineers and Data Scientists, and report to our Director of Data Science. You will develop key product and business insights for our clients as well as our internal teams, focused on all areas of the business.

You will propel WELL's data-driven analysis of ROI, best practices, and patient experience goals. You will be working with a rich data set drawn from hundreds of millions patient interactions across the United States.

This is an exciting opportunity if you are looking to take the next step in your Data career at a high-growth startup. You will have the opportunity to grow and learn from a tight-knit team of talented Data professionals.

Responsibilities
Develop a full list of relevant Customers', Vendors', and other Partners' metrics and underlying data
Map Customers', Vendors', and other Partners' data to WELL generated data model
Obtain and refresh Customers', Vendors', and other Partners' data related to specific metrics used in ROI calculation
Work collaboratively with Customer Success and Product to develop and maintain a set of best practices that drive these metrics
Develop credible and verifiable calculation and data validation that show the impact of WELL usage - generate testable conclusions with a solid understanding of logical traps like correlation vs causation, survivor bias, etc.
Work with Customer Success, Sales, and Marketing teams to deliver actionable insights based on verified customer data
Communicate with Customers, Vendors, and other Partners to understand their business goals and associated metrics
Innovate! Implement innovative quantitative analyses, try new data wrangling techniques, and experiment with new visualization tools


Requirements
Bachelor's degree in Mathematics, Statistics, Data Science, Engineering (or a relevant field of study)
3+ years of experience in Data Analytics and Business Intelligence (or a related role)
Advanced Excel / Google Sheets skills including functions, pivot tables, charts, and macros
4+ years of experience with SQL
3+ years of experience with business intelligence or data visualization tools
Some experience with ETL technologies such as Matillion
High-level understanding of how Machine Learning and Natural Language Processing works and able to consider their opportunities and limitations
Intermediate Knowledge and Skills around Statistics including probability, properties of distributions and statistics, interpretation of p-values, correlation, and basic modeling (such as linear regression)
Strong analytical and problem solving skills, with good business sense
Strong attention to detail
Passion for improving patients' healthcare experience and driven to understand the full set of WELL product capabilities from both a user and a technical perspective
Excellent written and verbal communication skills, along with strong presentation abilities
Solid project management and organizational skills

BONUS
Healthcare experience
Python skills
Experience with Looker
Customer support domain knowledge

LOCATION

WELL is headquartered in Santa Barbara, CA. Today, all WELL positions are remote, and we are looking forward to when our company returns to in-office work. We are open to candidates that are looking for a permanently remote role. Historically, remote team members visit the Santa Barbara office regularly, and we've found that works best when they are on the West Coast, specifically in Southern California.

WORKING AT WELL
Fantastic company culture – frequent Zoom company events (Lunch & Learns, trivia, yoga, etc.) and daily fun brought to you by many creative Slack channels.
Employee equity groups – 11 groups available for all to join. Black & Latinx, Women, LGBTQ+, Disability, and many more!
Learning and development – frequent events and tools available to help our employees #PursueGrowth.
Career mobility – we promote from within and have opportunities for employees to transfer between teams.
Santa Barbara office perks – dog-friendly office, healthy (and unhealthy) snacks, Kombucha and beer on tap, light-filled space, standing desks, and the occasional taco truck.
Company perks and benefits – MacBook Pro provided, unlimited PTO, generous equity package and full health benefits (medical, dental, and vision).

Interested in learning more? Please visit our LinkedIn page or our Life at WELL Instagram (@wellhealthinc). To hear firsthand what it's like to work at WELL, please view this team video.

Committed to Diversity, Equity, and Inclusion

WELL Health Inc. is an Equal Opportunity Employer and is committed to fair and equitable hiring practices. All hiring decisions at WELL are based on strategic business needs, job requirements and individual qualifications. All candidates are considered without regard to race, color, religion, gender, sexuality, national origin, age, disability, genetics or any other protected status.

We're dedicated to creating an inclusive, equitable, and diverse workplace, where everyone feels safe to be themselves and diversity is a strength. WELL is committed to providing employees with a work environment free of discrimination and harassment; WELL will not tolerate discrimination or harassment of any kind.

Title: Data Scientist (Remote)
Description:
ezCater is the world’s largest online marketplace for catering – a $60+ billion market just in the U.S. Businesspeople use us to find and order great food for meetings and events; restaurants and caterers use us to grow their catering business. We’re backed by Insight Partners, Iconiq Capital, Wellington, Lightspeed, and GIC, and in early 2019 were valued at $1.25 billion. COVID slammed us, but we responded by finding new customer segments and seizing the rare opportunity COVID offered: when in life does a very successful operation get a do-over? Come help us power Food For Work even better than we did it the first time.

Are you passionate about data? The Marketing team at ezCater serves hundreds of thousands of professionals feeding their teams with our platform - with data at the heart of decision making and strategic growth. We are expanding our Data Science capabilities across the team. Applying advanced statistical and Machine Learning methods to key optimization spaces, such as pricing, customer targeting, demand elasticity and LTV optimization, this role is critical to our mission of continuously improving the outcomes we provide to our customers.

As a member of the Marketing Data Science team, you will be working closely with business partners to address high-value and high-visibility problems from the position of market leadership in a fast-paced and fast-evolving industry. Data Scientists at ezCater draw from a strong peer group across multiple specialties for collaboration and have a modern ML Operations stack and team to ensure the work doesn’t end with a report, but lives in our product and decision making processes over the long term.

You Will
Leveraging a modern Data Science/ML Stack, use advanced analytical, modeling and simulation techniques to develop insights and systems that improve our ability to serve our customers and catering partners efficiently.
Expose patterns across structured and unstructured data to identify business opportunities, working with business partners on problems that will materially benefit our customers and our results.
Focus on end-to-end problem solving, working with business analysts and BI teams on exploratory analysis and Operations and Software engineering teams to productionalize model outputs.
Proactively identify opportunities for the application of Advanced Analytics and Machine Learning across the catering partner business - serve as an advocate for continuous improvement across the analytics space.
Contribute to ezCater’s culture of personal and professional growth by leading projects with multiple stakeholders and mentoring others in this valuable field.

You Have
Experience with both natural and controlled experiment design and a proven ability to solve and communicate complex problems using both technical skills and creativity.
Expertise and prior experience applying Python, R or similar programming languages within statistical modeling and ML spaces.
Experience working with common Python tools (e.g. Scikit-learn) preferred.
A proven ability to apply a scientific approach to building models, evaluating statistical outcomes and continuous improvement of your work.
Proficiency in SQL is required. A background in modern programming languages is preferred.
Ability to work independently and collaboratively.
Our data stack is Snowflake, DBT, Stitch, Airflow, AWS, Sagemaker, MLFlow, Kubernetes + Docker. Any experience with the above is a nice-to-have.
A sharp mind, a soft heart and a large funny bone.

What You’ll Get From Us

You’ll get a terrifically compelling opportunity, in an environment of radical transparency, open access to all the data, and collaborative colleagues at every level of our organization. You’ll also get sane working hours and great flexibility around work/life balance.

Have people in your life – of any age – who always, often, or sometimes need your help? We make room for that. Have a bad thing or a good thing happen to you? We make room for that, too.

Oh, and you’ll get all this: Market salary, stock options that you’ll help make worth a lot, the usual holidays, all-you-can-eat vacation, 401K with ezCater match, health/dental/FSA, long-term disability insurance, a great office in the heart of Boston or Denver that you can’t use till COVID lightens up, a tremendous amount of responsibility and autonomy, wicked awesome co-workers, cupcakes (and many more goodies) once we get back to our offices, and knowing that you helped get this rocket ship to the moon.

ezCater is an equal opportunity employer. We embrace humans of every background, appearance, race, religion, color, national origin, gender, gender identity, sexual orientation, age, marital status, veteran status, and disability status. At the same time, we do not employ jerks, even brilliant ones.

For information on how ezCater collects and uses job applicants' personal information, visit our Job Applicant Privacy Policy.

Title: Data Analyst (A/B Testing)
Description:
About Pushnami

🎉Named the #1 Fastest-Growing Company in Central Texas | Austin Business Journal

Pushnami is an Austin built and privately held technology company that provides an AI Powered Cross-Channel Messaging Platform used by thousands of websites around the world. We are seeking a passionate and energetic Customer Success Manager to aid in our client retention efforts. This individual will join us at our new Central Austin headquarters (a historic landmark, where they filmed a famous scene from the cult classic movie Dazed and Confused "alright, alright, alright").

Title: Data Analyst
Description:
DATA ANALYST
OFFICE OF ACCOUNTABILITY, OLIVER HODGE BUILDING, OKLAHOMA CITY, OKLAHOMA

Job Summary

Under the general direction of the Executive Director of Accountability and Assistant Executive Director of Accountability, provide technical assistance to Oklahoma State Department of Education staff, school administrators and other school district staff. We seek someone with strong analytic and communication (written, verbal, visual) skills, as Data Analysts play a vital role in interpreting data and communicating insights that affect decision-making. Data Analysts also support daily operations, including but not limited to: providing direct assistance to school district users; reviewing and auditing education data; assisting with federal and state data reporting requirements; and ensuring quality and consistency of data processes.

Required Education And Experience
Associate's degree from an accredited college or university (official transcripts required) in Computer Science, Mathematics, Statistics, Informatics, Management Information Systems, or related field dealing with quantitative data [official transcript(s) required];
Experience using structured query language (SQL) to query, manipulate, and analyze existing data.
Preferred Education And Experience
Bachelor's degree from an accredited college or university (official transcripts required) in computer science, mathematics, statistics, informatics, management information systems, education, or related field dealing with quantitative data [official transcript(s) required];
Experience using data management systems and analysis tools (e.g., SQL Server, Python, R, SPSS) or business intelligence systems (e.g., Power BI).
Knowledge/Skills/Abilities
Ability to work with Oklahoma public school district staff and leaders to support and improve the Office of Accountability's various data review and data reporting processes;
Ability to present facts and opinions clearly, concisely and objectively;
Ability to analyze situations correctly and to adopt an effective course of action;
Strong verbal and written communication skills;
Ability to lead, take the initiative, work independently and manage multiple responsibilities simultaneously, paying close attention to detail on many and varied tasks;
Ability to manipulate, validate, analyze, and report data using SQL;
Ability to analyze, manage, and support large datasets given established parameters;
General knowledge of programming logic and concept;
Knowledge of software development life cycle experience in system analysis activities (e.g. system requirements gathering, system requirements writing, production support, testing support);
Can critically evaluate information gathered from multiple sources, reconcile conflicts, and recommend solution ideas;
Knowledge of data literacy skills, including but not limited to: creating and interpreting data visualizations; engaging in root cause analysis processes; applying appropriate data analytics methods; recognizing misinterpreted or misrepresented data summaries; and communicating data-driven insights.
Position Responsibilities/Essential Functions
Serve as one of the first points of contact for public school administrators and other school personnel seeking assistance with the Office of Accountability's data review and reporting efforts;
Support district users in utilizing and navigating the state's Accountability Reporting application;
Work with leaders at the State Department of Education in the development and completion of reports, data review windows, and other analyses related to federal and state accountability requirements;
Maintain and develop quality control procedures for components of the Oklahoma Accountability System;
Maintain accurate logs of issues that need to be escalated to senior data analysts or other staff;
Maintain extensive personal calendar, scheduling and coordinating speaking engagements, conferences, and meetings;

Title: Data Analyst
Description:
The Democratic Attorneys General Association provides political and policy support to Democratic State Attorneys General in their mission to protect citizens, promote progress, and support civil rights.

Reports To: Data Science Director

Salary Range: $50,000 - $60,000

Purpose:

The Democratic Attorneys General Association (DAGA) is seeking a Data Analyst to join the Data, Technology, and Innovation (DTI) team at DAGA. The DTI team works to support Democratic Attorneys General and AG candidates throughout the country with quantitative and qualitative electoral research, guidance on voter contact universes, and our in-house analytics work on persuadable voters. The Data Analyst will report to the Data Science Director at DAGA and work collaboratively with all members of the DTI team to execute ongoing data projects and expand the scope of data offerings from the DTI team.

Primary Responsibilities:

Assist with the execution of statewide and national polling projects, including survey drafting, sampling, weighting, and topline and crosstabs creation
Conduct research on past election results, past electorate demographics, and current political issues as relevant for ongoing polling, modeling, and data analysis projects
Structure and design data visualizations to communicate data to internal stakeholders, campaigns, and strategic partners
Draft memos and presentations reporting out on focus group, polling, and analysis results
Build targeted voter contact universes off of demographic, modeled, and previous contact data using SQL in a Google BigQuery database
Other duties as needed, including assorted administrative duties contributing to data-related projects

Qualifications:

This is a fast-paced and fast-changing work environment; the ability to organize and handle multiple projects, set priorities and meet deadlines is required
Ability to interact with individuals at many levels and handle confidential matters
Excellent attention to detail required
Some prior experience (work or education, formal or self-directed) in data analysis required, preferably in SQL, R, or Python, but not required
Experience or willingness to learn data visualization programs such as Tableau or Google Data Studios
Proficiency with the Microsoft Office suite a plus, particularly Microsoft Excel and Microsoft Powerpoint
Willingness to learn new techniques and adapt to the existing codebase
Ability to communicate orally and in writing about data analysis and visualizations, especially to non-technical stakeholders
Previous experience with or exposure to political campaigns, voter research, or voter targeting a plus
Interest in public policy, politics, and electioneering
Humor, initiative, and openness to evolving responsibilities


Application Requirements:

Please submit resume and cover letter
There will be a skills test in SQL during the interview process. If you are interested, here are some resources:
https://sqlbolt.com/lesson/introduction
https://www.w3schools.com/sql/

DAGA's office is open 9 AM – 6 PM Eastern, but extended and nontraditional work hours are required.
DAGA offices are in downtown DC but are currently closed due to the COVID-19 pandemic. DAGA is currently accommodating remote work, although the position will likely be DC-based once DAGA reopens its office.
DAGA will work with potential candidates to schedule remote interviews and process onboarding procedures remotely, as necessary.
DAGA offers a generous benefits package that includes fully paid health, dental, vision, short-term, long-term, and life insurance policies, pretax spending accounts, monthly remote work stipend, or monthly transit benefit.

Title: Data Analyst, Impact Assessment
Description:
Job Summary

Soon to be part of the newly announced Bloomberg Center for Cities at Harvard University , the Bloomberg Harvard City Leadership Initiative is an ambitious joint effort of Harvard Kennedy School and Harvard Business School in close collaboration with and funded by Bloomberg Philanthropies to advance leadership, management, and innovation in cities. Now in its fourth full year, the Initiative equips mayors and senior city officials with the skills, tools, and techniques to tackle the leadership and management challenges they face in their cities. The initiative also aims to identify and fill gaps in research on city leadership, to generate new and customized curriculum, and to develop the next generation of city leaders through its work with students.

Going beyond satisfaction surveys, the Initiative measures impact by assessing the adoption of ideas in practice. The Initiative maintains a dedicated impact assessment function to
Learn what works in the programming to continuously evolve and improve;
Develop an evidence base for what works in practice; and
Remain accountable to program participants, the academic community, our donor, and the larger field of practice
The Data Analyst for Impact Assessment and Learning will play a critical role in executing data collection and analyses in support of evaluating, assessing, and communicating the impact of the Initiative.

We are committed to building and fostering a diverse and inclusive team of staff, students, and faculty and we seek candidates who share our commitment and values.

Job-Specific Responsibilities

The Data Analyst will report to the Initiative’s lead for Impact Assessment and Evaluation and will assist in rigorous analysis of qualitative and quantitative impact assessment data, and will be responsible for:
Adapting and administering program surveys and other quantitative measures
Conducting interviews and collecting other qualitative data
Analyzing qualitative and quantitative data
Using qualitative and quantitative data to make recommendations for continuous improvement
Storytelling with data through visuals and narrative to communicate with non-technical audiences
Reporting analysis to a variety of audiences including executive leadership.
Responding to requests for analyses and data from stakeholders at all levels
Developing processes for organizing and making data and analyses accessible to the Initiative’s team
Maintaining and building upon infrastructure and processes for systematic collection and analysis of data in close collaboration with the initiative’s operations team
Contributing to new impact assessment instruments and protocols
Engaging in ongoing learning through mentoring and professional development

Basic Qualifications

Bachelor’s degree (or equivalent experience) and 3 years of progressively responsible experience in Education, Statistics, Economics, Public Policy, Anthropology, Sociology, or other relevant field.

Additional Qualifications And Skills
Self-starter, with an enthusiasm for learning a variety of research and analysis work
Strong quantitative and qualitative analysis and design experience and motivation to learn or advance these skills
Curiosity about how executive education influences behaviors and actions of city leaders
Ability to examine problems from multiple angles to engage in creative and collaborative problem-solving
Experience analyzing and interpreting interviews or other qualitative data (experience with NVivo a plus)
Experience analyzing and interpreting survey results and working with smaller quantitative datasets (experience with R, Stata, or Excel Macros a plus)
Aptitude for storytelling with data through visuals and narrative
Experience using data to make recommendations for continuous improvement
Facility translating technical concepts for a non-technical audiences
Excellent interpersonal skills that resonate with audiences of different backgrounds
Strong team-player with an ability to build productive relationships and work across all levels across a diverse organization
Entrepreneurial work style with an enthusiasm for doing whatever it takes to get the job done.
Clear, concise, and persuasive oral and written communication
Master’s degree preferred

Lendly is seeking an experienced Senior Data Analyst to join our BI Analytics Team. The Senior Data Analyst will be tasking with performing various functions, including the creation and production of KPIs, BI Dashboards, ad-hoc reporting, and decision support analysis to evaluate the company’s overall performance.

·      Excellent interpersonal, verbal, and written communication skills and ability to communicate complex ideas and strategy to both external and internal clients

Education and Experience Requirements:

·      Bachelor’s degree in Math, Statistics, Computer Science, Economics, or other quantitative fields
·      2-4 years of experience as a data analyst working with business partners to drive quantitative analysis and recommendations.

Title: Data Engineer
Description:
Help Us Shape the Future of Healthcare.

As a Data Engineer , you help us build secure, scalable and reliable infrastructure and pipelines to support our growing data and Machine Learning needs. In this role, you will work as part of a small multi-disciplinary team to establish and evangelize the data and AI driven culture. This team will not only work with the product team closely but will also support non-engineering functions like Marketing and Business Strategy.

To thrive in this role, you are someone who works well in cross-functional teams and enjoys collaborating. Furthermore, you understand the business impact of your work and enjoy measuring and presenting it. You enjoy working with product management and other stakeholders to find the best solution to the problem at hand, iterate over it and can balance technical complexity with delivering customer value timely.

Our platform and applications run on Google Cloud. Our current pipelines are built with Airflow and Python and use MongoDB and PostgreSQL as the data store and warehouse. We are building a next generation DataLake on GCP. You will be working on building infrastructure for real-time and batch pipelines to ingest and transform data from a variety of sources. You will have an opportunity to experiment with new frameworks and paradigms, and freedom to put cutting-edge tech in production to shape the future of digital health!

In This Role, You Will
Translate business needs into data and analytics requirements, with attention to detail
Utilize a variety of distributed computing platforms and tools to build scalable ETL / machine learning pipelines to meet the team's objective
Analyze, tune, troubleshoot and support the data infrastructure ensuring the performance, integrity, and security of data
Use sound agile development practices (testing and code reviewing, etc.) to develop and deliver data products
About You
Build and maintain consistent, secure and performant data pipelines
Provide tooling for product analytics and data-science
Experience with software development on data pipelines and big-data technologies
You have experience in a cloud Data Stack - preferably GCP
Experience in orchestration tools like Airflow
Experience in developing pipelines using python
Experience in implementing deployments, error handling and monitoring for scalable pipelines
Experience in performing root cause analysis of production issues , performance tuning and optimization
Our platform and applications run on Google Cloud. We build our backend services with Go and MongoDB, our web apps with React and Redux, and native Android and iOS apps. We ship code to production every day, and we’re always looking to improve both the quality and speed of our releases. You may not have expertise in our particular programming languages or technologies, but that’s okay. What’s important to League is your ability to take ownership and solve problems, as well as your collaborative spirit and drive for professional growth.

At League, we’re big on building connections - both through our product and with each other. Our platform is consumer centric, personalized and always on. It’s a front door to healthcare that empowers people to live healthier, happier lives. Every day.

When you feel connected to our mission, values and the work you do, you’re driven to perform your best every day. When you feel connected to people you work with, you’re able to build meaningful relationships that last. Together, we share the ultimate goal of delivering better health outcomes for everyone.

The world has changed, and so has the way we work. We believe you can work where you work best (whether it’s in the office all the time, a few days a week, or none of the time), and still feel connected to our mission, values, purpose, and each other. League is headquartered in Toronto with a second office in Chicago and we believe in empowering Leaguers to work their way—anywhere that works for them in Canada and the US. We also have members of the Engineering team working with us remotely in Brazil!

When it comes to perks and benefits, one size never fits all. We’re flexible here at League so everyone has the choice to get exactly what they need. This includes unlimited PTO, competitive salaries, paid parental leave, a Lifestyle Spending Account, a Health Spending Account and more!

Everyone is welcome. Diversity makes us better, and we believe in building diversity across cultural identity, gender, sexual orientation, age and education, thought and experience. We are an equal opportunity employer, and we are committed to working with applicants requesting accommodation at any stage of the hiring process.

League, Cleveland Clinic collaborate to make employees healthier across North America

Title: Program Data Analyst
Company: Administrative Office of the United States Courts
Description:
Duties
Summary
This position is located in the Defender Services Office under the Office of the Deputy Director.

Responsibilities
This is a hands-on position and will require the ability to communicate and interact with project management staff and Defender Services Office (DSO) managers regarding customer-focused initiatives that involve data translation, integration development, and/or reporting. Specific duties of the position include, but are not limited to:
Supporting multiple, complex business intelligence projects and providing hands-on assistance with data modeling, data integration, and other development activities.
Designing, developing, and generating ad-hoc queries and reports to meet DSO, AO, and defender needs.
Ensuring that all recurring and annual reports are on time and accurate.
Creating various reports to facilitate the analysis and development of DSO agenda items, case budgeting projections, district reviews, and Criminal Justice Act (CJA) panel rep counts and costs as needed.

Developing, enhancing, managing, and monitoring processes that will integrate many datasets and develop new reporting and analysis standards and capabilities.

An experienced Contract Officer Representative for IT systems, including providing quality assurance for contractor work products, reviewing contractor invoices for accuracy and make timely payments is highly desired but not required.

Title: Data Analyst
Industry: Defense & Space Non-profit Organization Management Law Practice
Description:
The Democratic Attorneys General Association provides political and policy support to Democratic State Attorneys General in their mission to protect citizens, promote progress, and support civil rights.

Reports To: Data Science Director

Salary Range: $50,000 - $60,000

Purpose:

The Democratic Attorneys General Association (DAGA) is seeking a Data Analyst to join the Data, Technology, and Innovation (DTI) team at DAGA. The DTI team works to support Democratic Attorneys General and AG candidates throughout the country with quantitative and qualitative electoral research, guidance on voter contact universes, and our in-house analytics work on persuadable voters. The Data Analyst will report to the Data Science Director at DAGA and work collaboratively with all members of the DTI team to execute ongoing data projects and expand the scope of data offerings from the DTI team.

Primary Responsibilities:

Assist with the execution of statewide and national polling projects, including survey drafting, sampling, weighting, and topline and crosstabs creation
Conduct research on past election results, past electorate demographics, and current political issues as relevant for ongoing polling, modeling, and data analysis projects
Structure and design data visualizations to communicate data to internal stakeholders, campaigns, and strategic partners
Draft memos and presentations reporting out on focus group, polling, and analysis results
Build targeted voter contact universes off of demographic, modeled, and previous contact data using SQL in a Google BigQuery database
Other duties as needed, including assorted administrative duties contributing to data-related projects

Qualifications:

This is a fast-paced and fast-changing work environment; the ability to organize and handle multiple projects, set priorities and meet deadlines is required
Ability to interact with individuals at many levels and handle confidential matters
Excellent attention to detail required
Some prior experience (work or education, formal or self-directed) in data analysis required, preferably in SQL, R, or Python, but not required
Experience or willingness to learn data visualization programs such as Tableau or Google Data Studios
Proficiency with the Microsoft Office suite a plus, particularly Microsoft Excel and Microsoft Powerpoint
Willingness to learn new techniques and adapt to the existing codebase
Ability to communicate orally and in writing about data analysis and visualizations, especially to non-technical stakeholders
Previous experience with or exposure to political campaigns, voter research, or voter targeting a plus
Interest in public policy, politics, and electioneering
Humor, initiative, and openness to evolving responsibilities


Application Requirements:

Please submit resume and cover letter
There will be a skills test in SQL during the interview process. If you are interested, here are some resources:
https://sqlbolt.com/lesson/introduction
https://www.w3schools.com/sql/

Additional Information:

DAGA's office is open 9 AM – 6 PM Eastern, but extended and nontraditional work hours are required.
DAGA offices are in downtown DC but are currently closed due to the COVID-19 pandemic. DAGA is currently accommodating remote work, although the position will likely be DC-based once DAGA reopens its office.
DAGA will work with potential candidates to schedule remote interviews and process onboarding procedures remotely, as necessary.
DAGA offers a generous benefits package that includes fully paid health, dental, vision, short-term, long-term, and life insurance policies, pretax spending accounts, monthly remote work stipend, or monthly transit benefit.

Title: Data Analyst, Impact Assessment
Industry: Non-profit Organization Management Financial Services Hospital & Health Care
Description:
Job Summary

Soon to be part of the newly announced Bloomberg Center for Cities at Harvard University , the Bloomberg Harvard City Leadership Initiative is an ambitious joint effort of Harvard Kennedy School and Harvard Business School in close collaboration with and funded by Bloomberg Philanthropies to advance leadership, management, and innovation in cities. Now in its fourth full year, the Initiative equips mayors and senior city officials with the skills, tools, and techniques to tackle the leadership and management challenges they face in their cities. The initiative also aims to identify and fill gaps in research on city leadership, to generate new and customized curriculum, and to develop the next generation of city leaders through its work with students.

Going beyond satisfaction surveys, the Initiative measures impact by assessing the adoption of ideas in practice. The Initiative maintains a dedicated impact assessment function to
Learn what works in the programming to continuously evolve and improve;
Develop an evidence base for what works in practice; and
Remain accountable to program participants, the academic community, our donor, and the larger field of practice
The Data Analyst for Impact Assessment and Learning will play a critical role in executing data collection and analyses in support of evaluating, assessing, and communicating the impact of the Initiative.

We are committed to building and fostering a diverse and inclusive team of staff, students, and faculty and we seek candidates who share our commitment and values.

Job-Specific Responsibilities

The Data Analyst will report to the Initiative’s lead for Impact Assessment and Evaluation and will assist in rigorous analysis of qualitative and quantitative impact assessment data, and will be responsible for:
Adapting and administering program surveys and other quantitative measures
Conducting interviews and collecting other qualitative data
Analyzing qualitative and quantitative data
Using qualitative and quantitative data to make recommendations for continuous improvement
Storytelling with data through visuals and narrative to communicate with non-technical audiences
Reporting analysis to a variety of audiences including executive leadership.
Responding to requests for analyses and data from stakeholders at all levels
Developing processes for organizing and making data and analyses accessible to the Initiative’s team
Maintaining and building upon infrastructure and processes for systematic collection and analysis of data in close collaboration with the initiative’s operations team
Contributing to new impact assessment instruments and protocols
Engaging in ongoing learning through mentoring and professional development

Basic Qualifications

Bachelor’s degree (or equivalent experience) and 3 years of progressively responsible experience in Education, Statistics, Economics, Public Policy, Anthropology, Sociology, or other relevant field.

Additional Qualifications And Skills
Self-starter, with an enthusiasm for learning a variety of research and analysis work
Strong quantitative and qualitative analysis and design experience and motivation to learn or advance these skills
Curiosity about how executive education influences behaviors and actions of city leaders
Ability to examine problems from multiple angles to engage in creative and collaborative problem-solving
Experience analyzing and interpreting interviews or other qualitative data (experience with NVivo a plus)
Experience analyzing and interpreting survey results and working with smaller quantitative datasets (experience with R, Stata, or Excel Macros a plus)
Aptitude for storytelling with data through visuals and narrative
Experience using data to make recommendations for continuous improvement
Facility translating technical concepts for a non-technical audiences
Excellent interpersonal skills that resonate with audiences of different backgrounds
Strong team-player with an ability to build productive relationships and work across all levels across a diverse organization
Entrepreneurial work style with an enthusiasm for doing whatever it takes to get the job done.
Clear, concise, and persuasive oral and written communication
Master’s degree preferred

Title: Data Scientist (Remote)
Industry: Internet
Description:
ezCater is the world’s largest online marketplace for catering – a $60+ billion market just in the U.S. Businesspeople use us to find and order great food for meetings and events; restaurants and caterers use us to grow their catering business. We’re backed by Insight Partners, Iconiq Capital, Wellington, Lightspeed, and GIC, and in early 2019 were valued at $1.25 billion. COVID slammed us, but we responded by finding new customer segments and seizing the rare opportunity COVID offered: when in life does a very successful operation get a do-over? Come help us power Food For Work even better than we did it the first time.

Are you passionate about data? The Marketing team at ezCater serves hundreds of thousands of professionals feeding their teams with our platform - with data at the heart of decision making and strategic growth. We are expanding our Data Science capabilities across the team. Applying advanced statistical and Machine Learning methods to key optimization spaces, such as pricing, customer targeting, demand elasticity and LTV optimization, this role is critical to our mission of continuously improving the outcomes we provide to our customers.

As a member of the Marketing Data Science team, you will be working closely with business partners to address high-value and high-visibility problems from the position of market leadership in a fast-paced and fast-evolving industry. Data Scientists at ezCater draw from a strong peer group across multiple specialties for collaboration and have a modern ML Operations stack and team to ensure the work doesn’t end with a report, but lives in our product and decision making processes over the long term.

You Will
Leveraging a modern Data Science/ML Stack, use advanced analytical, modeling and simulation techniques to develop insights and systems that improve our ability to serve our customers and catering partners efficiently.
Expose patterns across structured and unstructured data to identify business opportunities, working with business partners on problems that will materially benefit our customers and our results.
Focus on end-to-end problem solving, working with business analysts and BI teams on exploratory analysis and Operations and Software engineering teams to productionalize model outputs.
Proactively identify opportunities for the application of Advanced Analytics and Machine Learning across the catering partner business - serve as an advocate for continuous improvement across the analytics space.
Contribute to ezCater’s culture of personal and professional growth by leading projects with multiple stakeholders and mentoring others in this valuable field.

You Have
Experience with both natural and controlled experiment design and a proven ability to solve and communicate complex problems using both technical skills and creativity.
Expertise and prior experience applying Python, R or similar programming languages within statistical modeling and ML spaces.
Experience working with common Python tools (e.g. Scikit-learn) preferred.
A proven ability to apply a scientific approach to building models, evaluating statistical outcomes and continuous improvement of your work.
Proficiency in SQL is required. A background in modern programming languages is preferred.
Ability to work independently and collaboratively.
Our data stack is Snowflake, DBT, Stitch, Airflow, AWS, Sagemaker, MLFlow, Kubernetes + Docker. Any experience with the above is a nice-to-have.
A sharp mind, a soft heart and a large funny bone.

What You’ll Get From Us

You’ll get a terrifically compelling opportunity, in an environment of radical transparency, open access to all the data, and collaborative colleagues at every level of our organization. You’ll also get sane working hours and great flexibility around work/life balance.

Have people in your life – of any age – who always, often, or sometimes need your help? We make room for that. Have a bad thing or a good thing happen to you? We make room for that, too.

Oh, and you’ll get all this: Market salary, stock options that you’ll help make worth a lot, the usual holidays, all-you-can-eat vacation, 401K with ezCater match, health/dental/FSA, long-term disability insurance, a great office in the heart of Boston or Denver that you can’t use till COVID lightens up, a tremendous amount of responsibility and autonomy, wicked awesome co-workers, cupcakes (and many more goodies) once we get back to our offices, and knowing that you helped get this rocket ship to the moon.

ezCater is an equal opportunity employer. We embrace humans of every background, appearance, race, religion, color, national origin, gender, gender identity, sexual orientation, age, marital status, veteran status, and disability status. At the same time, we do not employ jerks, even brilliant ones.

Title: Data Analyst
Description:
We are seeking two experienced professionals to fill roles as Business Data Analysts (BDA) whose primary goal is to assist in the design, testing, and coordination of a technical/data solution to meet a business need while supplying subject matter expertise support of those who manage, develop, test and implement the solution. The BDA works across business/technology teams to ensure alignment between business solution definition and the enterprise information architecture for the Excellus organization. The Business Data Analyst works collaboratively across the organization to assure coordination and implementation of solutions. The key aspect of these roles is to enhance the organization's ability with defining system behaviors through various methods including Gherkin training.

Essential Responsibilities And Accountabilities

All Levels

Level I
Works with Business SMEs, Business Sponsors and Stakeholders to ensure business requirements are clearly defined, documented and broadly communicated. Often, this includes writing a Business Requirement Document (BRD) and/or similar documents.

Works with other team/individuals in the organization (i.e. Data Integration Analysts, Information Design Architects, etc.) to identify appropriate sources of data that meet the business requirements as well as confirming data quality.

Participates in peer reviews of all Business Data Analyst deliverables including BRD, contingency solutions, test plan/cases and change requests.

Participates in data analysis activities with guidance from Data Integration Analysts, Information Design Architects and/or Test Engineer, as appropriate.

Meets with project teams to review project scope/progress and resolve project issues.

Supports solutions by participating in core team meetings and other relevant project meetings including managing agendas and minutes.

Participates, as appropriate, in Solution Design reviews, Technical Specification reviews, testing approach / test case reviews.

Partners with product owner to ensure a common understanding/awareness of status and needs related to communications with the business / sponsors.

Participates with project team as part of the defect resolution process. Provides clarification, changes to business rules and support of testing.

Participates in the Excellus mentoring programs and helps to on-board new staff.

Develops and maintains current knowledge and skills on industry and professional trends. Shares learning and coaching experience through knowledge transfers between peers and outside contractors.

Consistently demonstrates high standards of integrity by supporting the Lifetime Healthcare Companies’ mission and values, adhering to the Corporate Code of Conduct, and leading to the Lifetime Way values and beliefs.

Maintains high regard for member privacy in accordance with the corporate privacy policies and procedures.

Regular and reliable attendance is expected and required.

Performs Other Functions As Assigned By Management.

Level II (in addition to Level I essential responsibilities/accountabilities):
Actively participates with data analysis activities, including other Data Integration Analysts and/or Data Warehouse Testing Engineers resources when appropriate.
Actively participates in solution test case/plan review activities, including other Data Integration Analysts and/or Data Warehouse Testing Engineers resources as appropriate.

Directly negotiates with and functions as a liaison between business stakeholders and project teams.

Meets with management and project teams to review project scope/progress and resolve project issues.

Identifies contingency approaches as needed to address schedule revisions, resource adjustments, and work requirements.
Can utilize training in Defining System Behaviors including:
Defining a product vision
Identifying users
Creating and splitting/breaking down user stories
Developing user flow diagrams
Using Gherkin to define conditions of acceptance
Defining non-behavioral requirements

Familiar with prototyping activities that will ensure the business requirements will be met.

Ensures that changes to the enterprise data model within the EDW (or other database) consider the business needs and ability to report/query against the data model.

Participates in rotating on-call support schedule working with DW Operations team as level 2 support.

Responsibilities

Level III (in addition to Level II essential responsibilities/accountabilities)
Performs a leadership role in the organization:
Leads data analysis activities.
Leads on-boarding of new resources.
Acts as coach and mentor to Product Owners and roles (as needed) with respect to BDD practices required by the Excellus Enterprise Software Development Lifecycle (eSDLC).
Leads and coordinates user group release updates and information sharing sessions.
Champion the use of BDD in the organization
Delivers and executes the Defining System Behaviors training, focusing on the following areas:
Defining a product vision
Identifying users
Creating user stories
Splitting Epics into MMFs
User Flow Diagrams
Using Gherkin to define Conditions of Acceptance
Defining non-behavioral requirements
Demonstrates and applies an Agile mindset
Responsible for audits of solutions and/or testing activities – inspects project artifacts for compliance.


Note

Minimum Qualifications

We include multiple levels of classification differentiated by demonstrated knowledge, skills, and the ability to manage increasingly independent and/or complex assignments, broader responsibility, additional decision making, and in some cases, becoming a resource to others. In addition to using this differentiated approach to place new hires, it also provides guideposts for employee development and promotional opportunities.

Level I

Bachelor's degree in Computer Science, Information Technology or relevant field (or four additional years related work experience in lieu of bachelors).

Three years of business/data analysis or related experience.

Demonstrated business process development skills and strong problem-solving skills.

Strong team player with a high level of interpersonal skills.

Demonstrated skills in quality principles especially root cause analysis and problem solving.

Ability to interact favorably with internal and external audiences.

Knowledge of Healthcare Payer industry preferred.

Excellent written and verbal communication skills - highly effective communicator with a strong customer satisfaction orientation.

Skills for listening to others' needs and concerns and translating them into terms that people in a different area can understand.

Experience in meeting facilitation and collaboration

Knowledge of BI and Analytics.

Knowledge of database management system (DBMS) physical implementation, including tables, joins and SQL querying

Level II (in Addition To Level I Minimum Qualifications)
Five years of business/data analysis or related experience.
Demonstrated experience in full lifecycle BI/DW implementations.

Ability to combine data from multiple sources when needed for the analysis.

Demonstrated experience with Data Warehousing.

Demonstrated competence in facilitation and project leadership tasks.

Demonstrated experience in integrating enterprise applications.

Capable of successfully delivering on multiple projects and priorities simultaneously.

Ability to work effectively with minimal supervision and serve as a mentor to other team members.

Level III (in Addition To Level II Minimum Qualifications)

Eight years data processing or related experience.

Demonstrated ability to understand problems and business requirements and deliver end-to-end business intelligence and data warehousing solutions which address these requirements.

Demonstrated competence in staff leadership, facilitation, and project leadership tasks.

Demonstrated capability to take on strong leadership role with high levels of user interaction, data analysis, and solution delivery.

Extensive knowledge of decision support concepts.

Demonstrated strategic vision in alignment with business objectives .

Physical Requirements

Ability to travel across regions



The Lifetime Healthcare Companies aims to attract the best talent from diverse socioeconomic, cultural and experiential backgrounds, to diversify our workforce and best reflect the communities we serve.

Our mission is to foster an environment where diversity and inclusion are explicitly recognized as fundamental parts of our organizational culture. We believe that diversity of thought and background drives innovation which enables us to provide leading-edge healthcare insurance and services.With that mission in mind, we recruit the best candidates from all communities, to diversify and strengthen our workforce.

Our Company Culture

Employees are united by our Lifetime Way Values & Behaviors that include compassion, pride, excellence, innovation and having fun!We aim to be an employer of choice by valuing workforce diversity, innovative thinking, employee development, and by offering competitive compensation and benefits.

Equal Opportunity Employer

Education

Preferred

Bachelors or better in Computer Science.

Bachelors or better in Information Technology.

Bachelors or better in Review Required.

Title: Data Governance Analyst
Description:
Collibra/Data Management/Data Quality/Data Governance
  Core responsibilities include:
 -     Be part of Data governance integrations program from data engineering side.
   -     Participate in design, development of governance tools and technology solutions integration to Collibra, data catalog, Enterprise data lake, EDW, Data quality & Governance business needs.
   -     Help in creating data requirements, Data mapping, data quality rules & meta data definitions.
   -     Close interaction and collaboration with Project Managers, Lead Business Analysts, application and enterprise architects, application technical leads, vendor partners (both onsite and offshore), offshore developments teams and other data and application development teams.
      Required skills:
-     8+ years of experience as Data analyst and at least 4+ years of work experience with financial services domain.
-     5+ years’ hands-on experience in managing data projects within Financial Services / Asset Management particularly in one or more of the following topics: Data Governance, Data Profiling, Data Quality, Data Glossaries, Data Catalogs, Taxonomy, Data Modeling, Metadata, Data Discovery, Business Semantics
-     Must have 4+ years of hands-on experience implementing and using Collibra suite of tools (Governance, Catalog, etc.) to search metadata, establish data lineage, capture profiling statistics, build data quality scorecards, find relationships and similarities between data assets, and maintain business and technical glossaries.
-     Hands on experience in scripting & ability to write complex SQL queries to perform data analysis and user testing prior to actual UAT.
-     Solid understanding of Collibra API’s and their usage.
-     Solid understanding of data taxonomy ad their integration with data lake.
-     Solid understanding of metadata requirements and components.
-     Excellent understanding of semantics and their relationship to business data dictionaries.
-     Experience with and understanding of Data Quality principles and measurement.
-     Strong organizational skills and detail-oriented mindset.
-     BS in Computer Science, Information Systems, or a related field.
Coordinating and working along with Offshore resources.
