Title: Data Scientist
Description:
SGA's Data Analytics (DA) team requires a self-learning Data Scientist, to solve complex analytics problems for our US based global Media clients. Our team of 60+ Data Engineers + Data scientists already use multiple available open source and licensed tools in the market to solve complex problems and drive business decisions.  

What you will be responsible for - 
• Identify valuable data sources and automate collection processes
• Work directly with the stakeholders on analytics framework model building, database design, and deployment strategies
• Undertake pre-processing of structured and unstructured data
• Analyze large amounts of information to discover trends and patterns and present information using data visualization techniques
• Apply advanced statistical and predictive modeling techniques to build, maintain, and improve on multiple real-time decision systems
• Propose analytic solutions and strategies to business challenges
• Dive into data, clean it up, and pull-out insights that can be used to improve system performance and present to senior leaders with recommendations on business actions
• Develop and test models using appropriate tools and technologies and deploying the same in the production environment using continuous delivery practices 
• Assist the development team with productization of successful algorithms, ensuring your work continues to drive value at scale

What you should have - 
5+ years of overall industry experience specifically in data engineering and analytics
4+ years of experience building and deploying large scale data processing and analytics pipelines in a production environment 
Broad experience building different types of advanced analytic solutions, including some of the following: time series analysis, cluster analysis, tree-based algorithms, generalized linear models, text analytics, or neural networks
Strong experience in building data pipelines and analysis processes using Python and PySpark
Familiarity  with DevOps systems, such as GitLab
Understanding the concepts of API and their integration with any  coding language
Database architecture, maintenance and usage of Redshift
Experience with TB or PB size datasets preferred

Title: Payments Business Analyst, WhatsApp
Description:
Facebook's mission is to give people the power to build community and bring the world closer together. Through our family of apps and services, we're building a different kind of company that connects billions of people around the world, gives them ways to share what matters most to them, and helps bring people closer together. Whether we're creating new products or helping a small business expand its reach, people at Facebook are builders at heart. Our global teams are constantly iterating, solving problems, and working together to empower people around the world to build community and connect in meaningful ways. Together, we can help people build stronger communities - we're just getting started.

WhatsApp is a fast, simple and reliable way to talk to anyone in the world. More than 1 billion people in over 180 countries use WhatsApp to stay in touch with friends and family, anytime and anywhere. WhatsApp is not only free but also available on multiple mobile devices and in low connectivity areas — making it accessible and reliable wherever you are. It's a simple and secure way to share your favorite moments, send important information or catch up with a friend. WhatsApp helps people connect and share no matter where they are in the world.Payment Operations is a fast growing function within WhatsApp. We are seeking a strong business support analyst in the payments team sitting within Customer Operations to drive our customer support experiences in Brazil.

Responsibilities
Work across WhatsApp and Facebook cross-functional teams and external partners to design and implement robust Payments customer support experiences for our users
Conduct external research to ensure an optimized and benchmarked support experience for Payments. Collaborate for insights around the payments support ecosystem to Product Management, Engineering, and other cross-functional partners
Support the payments customer experience in a wide variety of workflows including multi-channel customer correspondence, user journeys, policies and compliance, reporting & analytics, tool & infrastructure development, new product testing, support and vendor management
Design, plan and project manage operational readiness for regional launches across Customer Operations and cross-functional teams (design, engineering, legal, risk, vendor management, infra, training, content, risk, data etc.
Process analysis and design for upcoming payment launches working closely with product, engineering, and internal community operations stakeholders
Act as a subject matter expert for incoming questions from teams across our family of apps on Commerce, Customer Support, and Operations
Coordinate data and tooling requirements for launches and work with infrastructure and tooling teams to prioritize and roadmap these requirements
Work directly with users and provide scaled support to resolve their issues, identify user trends, and work with cross-functional partners to resolve issues
Utilize problem solving skills to resolve large and complex business problems
Be an escalation point for life support of vendor teams dealing with commerce issues
Rollout and incubate new support processes and workflows, and leverage analytics and automation to build business cases and continuously improve processes
Design, manage & continuously improve KPIs and measure success across key commerce processes
Gather, analyze and use relevant data to develop ways to improve the overall commerce support experience
Minimum Qualification
5+ years of work experience in relevant payments, Fintech or operations fields
Experience with managing projects relating to process design, driving efficiencies, identifying gaps and implementing improvements
Experience with analytical problem solving of business operational challenges
Experience with relationship building and collaborating with a diverse, global, cross-functional team
Demonstrated experience working with ambiguity, adapting and learning new skill sets, and creating a solid understanding of operational challenges
Independent and thorough in examination and analysis, along with being consensus-building and results-oriented
Communication skills and demonstrated experience as an open, collaborative and proven team player
Organizational and time management skills
Fluent in Brazilian Portuguese and English Local language, with experience in the Brazilian market
Preferred Qualification
Experience in process excellence for payments platforms/industry

Summary

The candidate is expected to be a domain expert of supply chains and their use cases. Design critical analytical dashboards, reports and queries to drive strategic business decisions, ad-hoc analysis and identify descriptive and prescriptive solutions for internal Ryder teams and external customers. Dig deep into the core issues of business problems in order to drive a solution that gets at the heart of the causative problem. On this team, the Data Analyst will get the chance to be the expert of supply chain solutions, collaborating with other Data Analysts as well as Data Engineers and Data Scientists, using all the skills needed to exploit data to drive the business forward.

Essential Functions
Develop Dashboards by understanding business needs, interpret the integrated data and translate this into usable visualizations to drive business decisions, interpreting results and how to utilize the dashboards.
Engage the business, evaluating their needs and ad-hoc requests to prioritize product efforts creating new innovative solutions.
Enhance data maturity and integration to standardize the core value add functionality enabling a multiplier effect.
Experience working within a collaborative team. Helping more junior members to achieve success.
Challenge the status quo and help guide entrepreneurial innovation in both analytical products and the curation of new data sources elevating analytics beyond data reporting and dashboards to the delivery of actionable insights.
Knowledge of the Ryder Business, understanding the complexity of the supply chain world and the role that data has within this ecosystem.

Performs other duties as assigned.

Experience developing BI solutions with tools like Power BI and Tableau
Exposure using data manipulation and analysis tools like Alteryx and SSISExperience in writing queries using SQL
Experience working in an Agile structure with a focus on MVP and use case-driven solutions
Strong verbal and written communication skills, with an ability to express complex technical concepts in business terms
Support product innovation, working closely with technology throughout the build, test, and release of the product using agile methodologies

Bachelor's degree required in Supply Chain, Data Analytics or equivalent
Master's degree preferred in Supply Chain, Data Analytics, MBA or equivalent
Two (2) years or more Applied Project(s) experience in demonstrating, digital transformation, data management
Two (2) years or more experience in creating dashboards for diagnostic analysis across the business. Experience working in a cloud environment
Four (4) years or more working in an individual contributor role as a key member of the team that others rely on

Data Science & Analytics

Title: Product Data Analyst
Description:
About ForgeRock

In today’s highly connected digital world, understanding, managing and securing the identity of individuals and things is essential to safety and success of both businesses and their customers. Billions of people connect from anywhere, use a wide variety of devices and expect a seamless yet secure experience.

The ForgeRock mission is to provide the most simple and comprehensive Identity and Access Management Platform to help our customers deepen their relationships with their consumers and improve the productivity and connectivity of their employees and partners. Our identity solution enables great digital experiences and is embedded with a rich set of security, privacy and consent features. We deliver our platform through both cloud services and on-premises software.

Our customers are some of the biggest companies, organizations, and even countries in the world. On any given day, it’s likely that the ForgeRock Identity Platform helped keep your data safe, gave you access to stuff, and supported trusted relationships between you, companies and the devices you were using.

ForgeRock is headquartered in San Francisco, but we are a global company with offices in the following cities: Vancouver, WA; Austin, TX; Munich, Germany; London & Bristol, UK; Grenoble & Paris, FR; Oslo, NO; Singapore and Sydney, Australia. Please read more about us at forgerock.com or follow ForgeRock on Twitter at http://www.twitter.com/forgerock.

The Role

We are looking for a Product Analyst, who will play a key role in helping our product organization grow and scale using data insights. From building standard dashboards for key performance indicators to analyzing and understanding user behavior and product usage at a portfolio level to proactively identify improvements, this role is the perfect opportunity for someone who has an interest in both product management and analytics.

Responsibilities
Work cross-functionally within the Product organization to define and track appropriate KPIs for the commercial performance of the ForgeRock product portfolio
Build dashboards that empower quick data access and self-service for colleagues across different functions
Collaborate with Product and Success Managers to analyze usage and adoption trends to understand user behavior
Conduct in-depth analysis to understand the dynamics behind different KPIs proactively identifying opportunities for improvement.
Required Skills

& Qualifications
Degree in computer science, finance economics or any other analytical field.
Prior work experience in a reporting, analytics or business consulting role.
Excellent analytical / problem solving skills and the ability to synthesize large data sets and applying analytic frameworks for insights
Excellent written and verbal communication and presentation skills
Life At ForgeRock

We believe in and facilitate a flexible, collaborative work environment. We’re growing quickly, but remain true to the innovative, can-do startup values that got us here. Most importantly, we keep hiring talented, smart, fun, and genuinely nice people because that’s who we want to succeed with every day.

Here are just a few of the things that make ForgeRock special:

Title: Data Quality Analyst
Description:
Wiland is a leading marketing intelligence company serving many of the nation’s top companies and organizations. We provide solutions to thousands of clients in a wide variety of markets and industries. We use data and sophisticated analytics to predict marketing behavior. Our custom audiences and insights help organizations grow their business and improve profitability. We are committed to providing excellent service and products to our Clients.
                       We are seeking dedicated, high caliber professionals who are smart and energetic, have a positive attitude and take pride in their work. Currently, we have an opening for a Data Quality Analyst. The Data Quality Analyst is responsible for evaluating and ensuring data quality across Wiland’s various data sources. In addition, the Data Quality Analyst is responsible for planning and executing data tests, evaluation of change over time, and evaluation of new data. This includes studying and evaluating current reporting, utilizing and improving current data evaluation methods, writing test plans/cases, planning the test schedules, coordinating test resources, executing test cases, verifying test results, and maintaining a reusable library of test cases to support future testing. Tasks and responsibilities of the Data Quality Analyst position include:

Review and perform quality checks on existing data sources.
Review and perform quality checks of data performance in modeling and scoring.
Evaluate quality of licensed and acquired data.
Regular review of all standardized reporting about contact data and attribute data. Work with other analysts/teams as needed to accomplish the goal of assessing data quality. Analysis methodology should include standard analysis as well as use of Wiland proprietary methods of analysis.
Making recommendations to data owners about cadence of data build & rebuild based on analysis, drift evaluation, and other relevant analysis.
Study and test new ways to develop data using current tools, including partnering with owners of Wiland proprietary modeling platforms, with the goal of producing either (a) current data/datasets using improved methods or (b) new data/datasets using the established, performant methods or new methods.
Assist in leveraging existing data sources to their fullest potential for use in Wiland models and/or products.


Education, Experience & Qualifications:

Bachelor’s Degree or higher in business or a quantitative discipline (Business Data Analytics, Data Analysis, Statistics, Economics, Mathematics, etc.) or equivalent work experience. Must be able to produce college transcripts showing minimum 3.0 GPA.
2+ years of professional experience in applying data analysis in a business setting, with strong preference given to experience in direct and/or digital marketing. Experience with cooperative databases, circulation planning, advertising agencies, or brokers is a plus.
Experience with predictive modeling methods is a plus.
Solid quantitative and analytical aptitude and the ability to apply those concepts in a business setting, identifying relevant business questions and conceptualizing quantitative solutions (key measures, reporting, analysis, etc.).
2+ years of experience with Unix / Linux, MySQL or other relational database, as well as with R, Python or related statistical package, including extensive programming skills.
1+ years’ experience with databases, data access tools, and SQL.


Additional Details:

Location: Niwot, CO
Department: Product Management
Compensation Range: $56,000 - $70,000. Total compensation for this role also includes a variable component.
Our benefits include: Medical, Dental and Vision, Flexible Spending Account, Basic and Voluntary Life/ADD&D Insurance, Short & Long-Term Disability, 401(k) Retirements Savings Plan, Generous PTO Accruals and Designated Company Holidays.
Must be a US citizen or authorized to work in the United States.
Wiland is an equal opportunity employer.


Visit https://wiland.com/applicant-and-employee-privacy-notice/ for a description of the types of personal information we collect from applicants and employees and how we use it.

Title: Data Analyst Associate I/II (5-6)
Description:
Job Title/Grade: Data Analyst Associate I/II (5/6)

Reports to: Director, Global Strategic Marketing

Department: Global Strategic Marketing

Date: May 27, 2020

DAI is an international development company specializing in the development sector. For more than 45 years, we have worked on the frontlines of international development, tackling fundamental social and economic development problems caused by inefficient markets, ineffective governance, and instability. Currently, DAI is delivering results that matter in some 80 countries. Our development solutions turn ideas into impact by bringing together fresh combinations of expertise and innovation across multiple disciplines. Our clients include international development agencies, international lending institutions, private corporations and philanthropies, and national governments.

Function Of The Position

This is a full–time, professional position which will be working under the direction of DAI’s Director of Global Strategic Marketing. The Data Analyst Associate will support specific corporate efforts to improve data collection, management, and analysis of both external and internal DAI data. The majority of assignments will involve some combination of:
Identifying and testing various data sources
Creating a system to regularly capture data
Advising on best approaches to answer specific research questions using available data, including building analytical models
Advising on best channels to display and distribute analysis across global corporation

For illustration, the first assignment could be establishing new models for ingesting, cleaning, and analyzing market trend data in support of strategic planning and execution. This would involve comparing data sources for quality of information and ease of access; working closely with a data architect to extract, transform, and load the data, and building models and visualizations to make analysis user-friendly for a wide range of corporate employees.

Roles And Responsibilities
Scan new and existing data sources to determine relevance, reliability, and timeliness of information; recommend which sources are most relevant and reliable and easiest to harvest.
Assist in the creation of scalable, efficient, automated processes for large scale data analyses, model development, model validation and model implementation
Build automated systems to import data from selected sources and models to automate analysis
Build in checks that provide rigorous validation of the analysis to improve accuracy and reliability of gathered information
Ensure entire development lifecycle of all IT projects undertaken are documented, including the protocol, testing, methodology and processes developed
Develop template and resources of Business Intelligence (BI) dashboards for corporate use.


Qualifications

Minimum Qualifications:

Grade 5: 2 years of professional work experience and Bachelor’s degree or a Masters degree.

Grade 6: 3 years of professional work experience and Bachelor’s degree or 1 year and a Masters degree.
Experience connecting to and using a variety of external (3rd Party) data sets
Programming experience; ability to develop custom data scraping scripts using Python, R, or Java.
Experience building extract, transform, and load (ETL) tools ideally for large organizations.
Excellent communication skills (written and oral)
Creative and curious attitude
Strong critical thinking capabilities with an ability to rapidly assess situational needs, develop problem solving strategies, and implement sustainable solutions.
Ability to meet deadlines and take initiative
Must be able to work effectively in teams, including taking directions from others, being open to regular check-ins to show work progress, and contributing ideas and recommendations to enhance productivity

Equivalent combination of education and experience will be considered.

Preferred Qualifications
Experience with Microsoft data technology (Azure). Prior experience with SQL language.
Experience with packages such as NumPy, Pandas, Beautiful Soup, or RVest.
Interest in training and teaching data skills to a global work force
Knowledge of database architecture and ability to maintain a large volume of data over time.

Supervisory Requirements: None

DAI and its employees are committed to confronting racism and holding ourselves accountable for positive change within the company and in the communities, cultures, and countries in which we live and work. DAI is committed to attracting and retaining the best employees from all races and backgrounds in our continued effort to become a better development partner.

DAI upholds the highest ethical standards. We are committed to the prevention of sexual exploitation, abuse, and harassment as well as other ethical breaches. All of our positions are therefore subject to stringent vetting and reference checks.

DAI is an equal opportunity/affirmative action employer with a commitment to diversity. All qualified applicants will receive consideration for employment without regard to race, color, religion, sex, sexual orientation, gender identity, national origin, disability, or status as a protected veteran.

Title: Data Analyst
Industry: Marketing & Advertising Information Technology & Services Computer Software
Description:
Aderant is launching a new business that leverages data to provide transparency, insights and improvements in efficiency. Be a part of a brand new, highly collaborative team whose mission it is to bring innovation to the industry.

Aderant, is a software house providing business management software for legal firms. Our talented and enthusiastic staff mean that we have become a trusted partner to firms of all sizes, from boutique firms based in one office, to global organizations spanning four continents. While our legacy has been providing on-premises software, we’re also embracing the opportunities presented by cloud services and taking advantage of them.

As a Data Analyst, you will have the opportunity to be part of a new team and bring new and innovative insights to law firms globally, leveraging data about cases, timekeeping, financials and other operations. Your work will impact all members of the law firm from lawyers to the finance department.

Responsibilities
Determining and driving how that data is introduced to our customers (visualizations, dashboards, data packages, etc.).
Collaborate with data scientists and development engineers in building new or expanding existing offerings.
Applying analytical techniques to data unearthed by our data scientists to determine and display the potential value to our customers.
Oversee the launch of new data service offerings, including coordinating with other teams to ensure success.
Interact with customers and potential customers to understand relevancy of data/offerings the team is proposing and validate ideas.
Conducting ad-hoc research and analysis, and subsequently presenting results in a clean, clear, and actionable manner.
Skills

& Qualifications
Bachelor’s degree, preferably in Economics, Business, etc.
2-4 years relevant experience in an analyst or product role.
Experience managing business projects.
Expertise in translating strategic questions into tactical work plans and outputs.
Proficiency in Microsoft Office, in particular Excel and PowerPoint.
Experience with data visualization tools; Power BI a plus.
Experience in data science and/or data analytics a plus.
Culture

Our purpose is to help law firms excel and to improve people’s lives. Our commitment to each other is to foster a culture of innovation, collaboration, and personal growth where challenging the norm is celebrated.

Culture unites and defines our global company. We encourage our diverse workforce to bring their whole selves to work - ideas, experience, and passion to drive our business forward. From entry level to experienced professional, our environment supports connection, the human kind.

Title: Data Analyst - The Orchard
Description:
Overview

The Orchard is a leading music distribution company operating in over 40 markets worldwide – distributing music from independent artists including Ozuna, Skepta, Jorja Smith, John Prine, and Kelsea Ballerini. With cutting edge operations and an unparalleled global team, The Orchard partners with labels of all sizes to make their music and video available across hundreds of digital and physical retailers around the world. At The Orchard, the focus is to provide a comfortable, social and engaging environment to encourage productivity and creativity.

The Orchard is hiring a Data Analyst to join our New York team.

What You’ll Do

Reporting to the Director, Analytics, The Orchard has an immediate opening for a full-time Business orientated Data Analyst. As an analyst you will support a number of different teams, from Label Management to Sales and Marketing, to provide insight to enable a broad understanding of our business. Success in this position requires a strong ability to communicate and collaborate within the team and with internal stakeholders across The Orchard.
Prioritize business requests and accurately scope out the level of effort from a development perspective
You will deliver high-level business reviews for our top labels and artists, working with content acquisition, label management plus the marketing teams.
Build upon a set of existing data models to meet internal user needs
Understand business needs and facilitate technical solutions that provide efficient and streamlined access for business users
Provide subject matter expertise in collaboration with the product and engineering teams to provide best in class analytic solutions for our clients.
You will have the opportunity to provide any training on our internal data tools to various staff members where needed.
In addition you would liaise with global counterparts when required for further insight and understanding and also to report any data irregularities.
Who You Are
1-3 years’ professional experience working as an analyst with a focus on business solutions
SQL Expert
Familiarity with BI tools such as Looker, Tableau, Alteryx, etc
Experience with data modeling preferred
Experience using dbt and LookML preferred
Familiarity with Python or other scripting language preferred
A passion for data, especially for creating efficient and scalable models
An ability to extract the essence of a business request across various disciplines and translate those needs into a data solution
The ability to work independently and effectively communicate successes and roadblocks across various teams
Curiosity about unfamiliar data sets, and once they become familiar, new ways to model that data to create self-service analytics solutions
Working knowledge of the music industry, and an understanding of the current music consumption landscape
What We Give You
You join an inclusive, collaborative and global community where you have the opportunity to fuel the creative journey
A modern office environment designed to foster productivity, creativity, and teamwork
An attractive and comprehensive benefits package including medical, dental, vision, life & disability coverage, and 401K + employer matching
Voluntary benefits like company-paid identity theft protection and resources for pets, mental health and meditation resources, industry-leading fertility coverage, fully paid leave for childbirth or bonding, fully paid leave for caregivers, programs for loved ones with developmental disabilities and neurodiversity, subsidized back-up child and elder care, and reimbursement for adoption, surrogacy, tuition and student loans
We invest in your professional growth & development
Time off for a winter recess
About The Orchard

The Orchard is committed to providing equal employment opportunity for all persons regardless of age, disability, national origin, race, color, religion, sex, sexual orientation, gender, gender identity or expression, pregnancy, veteran or military status, marital and civil partnership/union status, alienage or citizenship status, creed, genetic information or any other status protected by applicable federal, state, or local law.

Title: Data Analyst
Description:
Job Description Header 2Web Marketing Data Analyst Irvine, CA contract to hire Job ID 2021-5369 Solugenix is assisting a client, a leading financial services company, in their search for a Google Analytics Data Analyst. This is a contract to hire opportunity based out of Irvine, CA. This will start remote, then transition onsite post covid.

The Google Analytics Data Analyst will collaborate with our Digital Marketing leader to help them understand the stories and insights hidden within our numerous online campaigns. Utilizing Google Analytics becoming the subject matter expert of that data set, it is essential that this role quickly gain a thorough understanding of our online marketing data and use that knowledge to intelligently communicate actionable recommendations to the Marketing business leaders.

Proficiency in Google Analytics, Google Tag Manager, and Google Data Studio Proficiency in Excel, PowerPoint, Power BI, and Tableau required.

Ability to manipulate large unstructured and structured datasets to build insightful solutions to complex problems and present the results in visually engaging and intuitive reports and dashboards. Demonstrated ability to communicate effectively to all levels of management. Strong skill in project management, communications, multi-tasking, and the ability to work independently. Sense of responsibility to self, team, and client. Outstanding integrity, initiative, creativity, and passion. Strong communications and collaboration skills.

Assist with the forecasting and tracking of monthly marketing performance vs budget. Coordinate with reporting teams and IT to operationalize successful forecast and analysis processes.

Our history was built on a foundation of partnerships with global brands like McDonaldrsquos, Microsoft, CIT Group, Johnson

Johnson, Herbalife, Sony Pictures Entertainment, and many others who look to Solugenix to be their trusted partner in providing professional staffing, non-IT and IT solutions.

Title: Data Analyst
Description:
Looking for an exciting, challenging opportunity to take your Data Analyst career to the next step? Seeking a fast-paced, government contracting environment where skill and motivation are rewarded, team work and a can-do attitude are expected, and a work-life balance is valued? Then we have the perfect position for you!

Spider Strategies has an opening for a talented, experienced Data Analyst to join our government contracting team.

** Must have a DOD SECRET (or interim) clearance and prior experience working with the US Army.**

Job Description

Serves as a Data Analyst and consultant on a strategic dashboard and business intelligence platform, focusing on manipulation, analysis and presentation of data as per client requirements.

This is a full-time position working from a government provided work site in Arlington, VA (Crystal City).

You will support our customer as a consultant, aligning strategy with data, designing processes to manage disparate data sets, and building dashboards that provide meaning; allowing for the most informed decisions to be made by senior leaders.

Other tasks involve such actions as supporting strategic review meetings, developing and leading training engagements, and working with customers to execute their strategic mission.

Requirements

Demonstrated understanding of qualitative and/or quantitative methods for assessment of planning and operations effectiveness and improvement of complex management processes and systems; the use of strategic planning and management techniques (such as dashboards and strategy maps) is a key factor.

This position requires an understanding of databases, SQL, primary keys, relational integrity, and how to manipulate raw data sets (Excel, CSV, XML, JSON, etc.).

The preferred candidate has a strong understanding of Military force structure (both administrative and war fighting), military readiness systems, Army-related regulations/publications, and of a wide range of techniques for management of highly complex functions and processes.

Excellent written and oral communication skills are a must in order to prepare concise recommendations, reports, and briefings to senior-level agency officials.

Capability to plan, organize, and complete studies and analyses related to assigned actions.

Must have a college degree.

Salary And Benefits

Salary will be determined based on experience. Spider Strategies offers great benefits, including a simple IRA, Flexible Spending Account, industry leading employee benefits, and a great work environment.

How To Apply

If you've got what it takes, we want to hear from you. To apply for this position, please apply through ZipRecruiter and provide your resume.

Spider Strategies is a leading provider of performance management software and consulting and supports some of the world's largest companies and U.S. Federal Agencies. In addition to rewarding work, working at Spider Strategies is rewarding. Spider Strategies was recently named one of the Top 10 "Best Places to Work" in the Washington, DC area by the Washington Business Journal -- this is Spider's 4th time to receive this recognition.

Title: Data Analyst - Naviguard Minnetonka, MN or Telecommute
Description:
As a Data Analyst you will be in a unique position to assist a growing business proactively plan, react to new developments, and implement improvements across multiple departments. Your work will involve looking at operational performance, business efficiencies, and uncovering medical cost drivers. You will have a strong understanding of medical claims and unit cost. You will investigate key business problems in several functional areas and provide leadership with quantitative analyses of healthcare cost and utilization data. You will analyze and uncover drivers of trends impacting cost and operations. You will analyze and interpret data from various sources, identify appropriate measurement methodologies, design reports, and work with technical, operational, and payment teams to drive performance. Your analyses will be used to create viable, real – world solutions in a complex health care landscape. To be successful in this role, candidate will have a strong attention to detail with the ability to quickly identify, analyze and solve problems. This position will report to the Director Data & Analytics.

Primary Responsibilities
Conduct analysis designed to identify root causes and produce recommendations
Communicate analysis including trends and opportunities to clients and the business in writing and verbally to solve complex business problems while negotiating multiple daily priorities
Collaborate with leaders of strategic initiatives to drive analytic information into business actions
Prepare daily/weekly report out to leadership on operational performance and key performance indicators (KPI’s)
Gather and document requirements from the client/business while focused on process improvement, workflow, benchmarking and/or evaluation of business processes
QA/analysis of large data sets used for reporting and QA/analysis of subsequent deliverables
Develop comprehensive understanding of programs being measured
Predict emerging business needs and develop innovative solutions to meet them
Working with relational databases, database structures and SQL queries on a daily basis
Work independently to manage competing priorities and requests
Complete ad hoc analysis as requested by internal customers


Basic/Minimum Qualifications
Bachelor’s degree in Data Science, Computer Science, Engineering, Actuarial Science, Statistics, Finance, Mathematics, Health Administration or related field
Experience working in an Enterprise Data Warehouse environment or multiple source data warehouse
Direct experience using SQL or similar tools to manipulate and evaluate data from relational databases


Preferred Qualifications
Power BI/ Tableau development and data visualization techniques
Healthcare provider contracting analysis and/or understanding of common reimbursement methods used for commercial medical insurance payments
3+ years of Healthcare Analytics or similar analytic experience
3+ years of experience using SQL query techniques to access relational databases
3+ years using medical claims data including hospital, ancillary, and physician.
Willingness to adapt to a continuously changing environment with changing priorities
Experience in prioritizing work on multiple complex assignments with ongoing deadlines
Demonstrated effective interpersonal, influence, collaboration and listening skills
Demonstrated ability to communicate ideas clearly and concisely in writing and verbally to individuals and groups
Highly motivated individual with a passion for helping the organization to navigate the complex healthcare system
Adaptability and flexibility to thrive in a startup environment

Title: Data Analytics Analyst I - Remote
Description:

Perform moderate level of data and statistical analysis in support of creating and shaping strategic decisions, dashboards, and other business related activities. Support line of business for all quantitative needs to include leading small to mid-size initiatives. Relies on senior analyst on limited basis for technical and business related inquiries. Title: Data Analyst
Description:
Job Description

Arena is a rapidly growing political marketing agency looking to hire an experienced, highly motivated, resourceful, and hardworking individual to join our growing Data Analytics & Reporting team as a Data Analyst.

The position would work closely with the Data Analytics & Reporting team to manage the execution of digital ad reporting, optimizing and debugging complex data flow and ETL (extract, transform, load) processes, and contribute insights and knowledge inside and outside of the department. Desired experience includes strong technical ability, excellent attention to detail and accuracy, the ability to juggle multiple projects and priorities, and the capacity to adapt and grow with the position.

The most important attributes are both a passion and ability to solve complex problems, and the ability to share your insights and knowledge with others.

Duties/responsibilities Include But Are Not Limited To
Identify, communicate, troubleshoot, and resolve data quality issues affecting fulfillment of business requirements
Mentor members of the analytics team and provide assistance to ensure efficient and effective execution of diverse responsibility portfolio and maintain high standards
Collaborate with department director to evaluate, design, and build improvements to existing data warehousing, reporting, and analytics infrastructure and systems
Communicate with company stakeholders to identify data-based insights to better allow colleagues and clients to understand and leverage data quickly and effectively
Extract and communicate actionable intelligence from structured data in SQL Server as well as unstructured data using advanced data mining techniques
Develop clear and well-structured analytical plans to conduct experiments, evaluate data sources, design innovative KPI metrics, and analyze datasets for critical insights
Liaise with other departments to understand project requirements, guide and develop interdepartmental processes to improve data quality, and guide the appropriate and effective use of data to improve overall company performance

Qualifications
Bachelor’s degree a plus
2-4+ years working in data analytics, data science, or data warehousing with proven business intelligence experience
Demonstrated experience writing T-SQL queries (including DDL, DQL, DML, and DCL), views, stored procedures, and functions to accomplish analytical tasks as well as troubleshoot and resolve issues in complex data flow processes
Demonstrated experience in Excel as well as Datorama to extract and present insights thoughtfully from large datasets
Must be extremely self-motivated and be a proactive and inquisitive learner to seek out skills and knowledge to enhance a line of inquiry or implement processes, and must have a strong ability to mentor others and share these skills or knowledge
Skilled at end-to-end quantitative thinking and excellent problem-solving skills with strong attention to detail and accuracy
Outstanding verbal and written communications skills with both technical and non-technical colleagues, efficient in working as part of a team, and able to translate between raw data and business KPIs
Excellent organization, time management, and prioritization skills to manage multiple projects simultaneously to meet objectives and key deadlines

Title: Data Analyst
Description:
Who We Are

WillowTree is one of the largest independent digital consultancies in the US building and designing digital flagship products crucial to our clients' business needs. We consult with Fortune 500 companies all over the world, such as HBO, National Geographic, Anheuser-Busch, PepsiCo, and more.

WillowTree is a 8-time Inc 500/5000 company and has been featured in the Forrester Wave for mobile, digital design, and development services. Recently, we were named to Deloitte's Technology Fast 500 for the second year in a row due to our 219% revenue growth from 2017-2019. We are also one of a few firms globally to be certified partners with Apple, Google, SAP, and Microsoft.

The Opportunity

As a Resource Manager at WillowTree, you'll collaborate across our company to coordinate project schedules and build multidisciplinary project teams. You'll guide both micro and macro decisions of Business Operations— from staffing requests on a single project to hiring needs for an entire office. You'll get a bird's eye view of a fast growing and well established business.

We understand our responsibility to create a diverse, equitable, and inclusive place within the tech industry, while pushing to make our industry more representative. Because of this responsibility, we need candidates who value diversity and inclusion through their work, team collaboration, or mentorship. So in your cover letter, we encourage you to reflect on diversity, equity, and inclusion.

In response to the pandemic, our team members have the option to work remotely. Once it is safe to return, this role will be based in our Charlottesville, VA office. Non-local candidates are encouraged to apply as we provide relocation assistance.

Responsibilities
Use internal business tools to manage project staffing and finance operations
Conduct air traffic control around project resourcing and financial details (kickoffs, delays, budgeting)
Create dashboards for internal stakeholders that communicate insights like utilization trends, unallocated resource reporting, and staffing needs
Support delivery teams in communicating allocation requests and decisions
Identify and evaluate pain points to provide recommendations that improve our process over time


Qualifications
2+ years of experience in a resourcing role (experience managing demand and capacity, overages, budgets, team member allocation, etc.)
The ability to analyze complex problems and simplify solutions
You can adapt to shifting priorities and make informed decisions
Experience communicating to various levels of stakeholders and tailoring your message based on audience
Ability to manage spreadsheet tools such as Excel or Google Sheets
A high level of empathy and curiosity

Bonus Points
Experience working with technical projects (understanding of the SDLC, allocating software projects)
Expertise with Enterprise Resource Management software or similar
Previous Project Coordination or Management experience
Experience transforming data into insights


Even if you don't have expertise in all of the qualifications listed, we value new perspectives and backgrounds and encourage you to apply. We're committed to building a diverse company that reflects the diversity of our users. We're committed to growth-mindset.

Why WillowTree?

We offer a place to be yourself.

Our differences, both visible and invisible, benefit our teams, our communities, and the products we craft. That's why WillowTree strives to build a team with diverse backgrounds, skills, and perspectives. You'll work hard here; however, we'll balance that with a culture that supports your growth and cares about your well-being. We're committed to creating an environment of inclusion — a place where every Tree can thrive.

We want you to reach your fullest potential and part of your professional development at WillowTree will include dedicated time to innovate on passion projects and an annual stipend to fund your professional pursuits.

WillowTree upholds our core values in every aspect of our work. We promote safe and inclusive work environments and maintain a drug-free workplace. We celebrate our differences and provide equal employment opportunities to all team members and applicants without regard to race, color, religion, age, sex, national origin, disability status, genetics, protected veteran status, sexual orientation, gender identity or expression, or any other characteristic protected by federal, state or local laws. Diverse teams build better products. We acknowledge that the tech industry especially lacks opportunity for those who are of non-traditional backgrounds and in underrepresented groups. In order to create the best products for everyone, we know that it's important for our team to reflect the diversity of our users, and we are committed to being the change we want to see.

Title: Data Analyst
Description:
Job Title: Data Analyst

Location: Anywhere in the US (Remote)

About InMarket

inMarket is the leader in digital advertising and predictive location solutions that help brands sense and respond to consumer needs in real-time. Since 2010, inMarket has helped thousands of brands leverage SDK-derived, opt-in consumer data to better understand who consumers are, why they make decisions and how best to reach them.

With inMarket's suite of solutions, brands can better understand consumers, activate real-time digital advertising in the moments that matter and generate better campaign attribution.

inMarket's Moments solution drives an average of 5x the performance of traditional digital media and was a key factor in winning Best Mobile Marketing Platform at the 2019 Digiday Awards. inMarket, headquartered in Los Angeles, has offices in Atlanta, Bentonville, Chicago, New York and San Francisco. inMarket is seeking a talented and motivated Data Analyst to join our Data Engineering team. You will work with petabytes of information and be responsible for building and maintaining dashboards, performing analysis and research into questions that arise from the reports, help optimize existing production algorithms, and be the go-to person for a plethora of ad-hoc requests that come in on a daily basis.

You will be a problem solver and investigative specialist. You will leverage your SQL expertise to find patterns, recognize problems and tease out insights from large amounts of data. You will be an expert at understanding how both internal teams and external clients analyze and interpret data so that you can provide recommendations and continue to iterate upon existing reporting products and develop new products. You should have a learning mindset and be passionate about bringing large datasets together to answer business questions and provide recommendations based on data and metrics.

Bachelor's degree in a quantitative field preferred (e.g. Computer Science, Economics, Mathematics, Physics, Engineering, etc.)

Experience with at least one programming language (JavaScript, Python or Scala preferred)
Experience with Spark and notebooks (Juptyer or Zeppelin) a plus
Strong data analysis, communication and presentation skills
Ability to translate complex business systems into technical requirements and executable code


Desired Qualifications
Able to balance expectations from many projects and stakeholders
Excellent analytical, and visualization skills
Great written and verbal communication skills
Ability to tell a convincing data story

Description

Humana is excited to announce the opening of a brand new contact center in Oklahoma City, OK! Humana has been awarded a contract to support the Oklahoma Medicaid population with its Healthy Horizons of Oklahoma statewide Medicaid program, and we need amazing individuals to join Humana in supporting OK Medicaid providers.

Humana is looking to have the entire team ready to support Oklahoma Medicaid providers starting mid-late summer.

The Provider Experience Advocate Data Analyst will analyze data gathered from the voice of the providers to provide insight to assist in improving provider experience. This individual will utilize multiple methods to analysis data from Provider Net Promotor Score (NPSt) which includes call listening, provider outreach, and insight and best practice identification. This role is vital to ensure Humana provides the best provider experience possible for the Oklahoma market.

Data analysis of Provider Net Promotor Score (NPSt)
Identify trends and insights from the data
Analyze the VOC transcripts and results for opportunities and issue resolution

Collect insights from call listening sessions
Create VOC improvement plans for agent opportunities
Utilize enterprise reporting on First Call Resolution, Top 400 providers, etc. to gain additional insights and opportunities
Identify opportunities to improve provider self-service.
Root cause resolution/outbound call to resolve frequently called about medical claims

COME GROW WITH HUMANA! BENEFITS DAY ONE – STELLAR 401K MATCH – PAID TIME OFF – TUTION ASSISTANCE PROGRAMS – STELLAR WELLNESS/REWARDS PROGRAM

Prior experience working in a fast pace environment successfully meeting goals and effectively communicating to all levels of leadership.
Must currently reside in the state of Oklahoma

Must have the ability to provide a high speed DSL or cable modem for a home office (Satellite and Wireless Internet service is NOT allowed for this role). A minimum standard speed for optimal performance of 10x1 (10mbs download x 1mbs upload) is required.
A dedicated work space without ongoing interruptions to protect member PHI / HIPAA information.

What you need to be STAND OUT among the crowd! : Preferred Qualifications
5+ years of experience with analyzing and reporting data and identifying root cause analysis or trends
3+ years of experience utilizing Tableau, Power BI, or other reporting databases on a daily bases.
Prior experience in healthcare industry

Title: Data Analytics Engineer
Description:
At Backstage (www.backstage.com), we’re focused on providing the best career platform to match performing artists and crew with talent seekers in film, television, commercials, branded content, theater, and more worldwide. 

We are searching for a Data Analytics Engineer who can confidently build and maintain quality ETL processes. This person will own a majority of the analytics data stack and work closely with the BI team to provide insights across the rapidly expanding international team at Backstage. The role requires the technical knowledge to transform, optimize and store data; as well as impeccable communication skills to document and ensure data is interpreted correctly.

As the Data Analytics Engineer, you will be responsible for building, maintaining and optimizing ETL processes that feed Backstage’s analytics. The BI team will rely on you to investigate python production code, read API documentation and work with developers to build an understanding of how information is specifically being collected. With this knowledge in hand, you will work with the analytics, finance, marketing and/or product teams to determine how the information should be transformed into a data model that is relevant to the business. You will need advanced SQL skills to transform data from multiple sources; and strong communications skills to clearly document and explain the final data model. There is a significant amount of analytical data infrastructure to build for a growing team, so you will need to balance priorities, meet deadlines and make sure you are investing enough time to make data models sustainable and easy to repurpose in the future.   

Requirements and Responsibilities:
3+ years professional experience in a data engineering or equivalent role
Strong proficiency in writing advanced SQL queries and leveraging core logic skills to transform data  
Experience working with relational databases, query authoring (SQL) and familiarity with a variety of databases 
Experience interpreting data from a variety sources from backend data to web engagement to third-party data 
Ability to communicate how data models should, and should not, be used for analytics 
Documenting processes and data structure for business users 
Solving your task at hand while maintaining an awareness on how you will repurpose and evolve your data models in the future 
Ensuring data stability with testing 
Building a DAG processes using dbt, Airflow or equivalent
Optimizing large tables in Redshift and its Spectrum service

Bonus:
Experience setting up data piping in Stitch and/or leveraging AWS Glue
Familiarity with modern web-based businesses and an understanding of common metrics and measurement techniques, including A/B testing

Backstage is the leading platform in creative talent placement in the United States, United Kingdom, Australia, Canada, New Zealand and Continental Europe. Backstage properties include Backstage, Mandy, and StarNow for hiring actors, models, voiceover artists, and crew; and Sonicbids, for booking musicians -- with plans to launch additional verticals organically, through acquisition, and by expanding to new markets across the globe. Nowhere else will you find the same combination of startup energy, trailblazing innovation, and entertainment industry creativity built upon the solid foundation of one of the industry’s most beloved and recognized names.

We are a passionate, agile team who are disrupting the creative talent placement marketplace through product-first design, leading technology, and a proven business model. At the heart of our success and growth are a tight-knit group of hardcore technologists, writers, marketers, and product designers who believe that collaboration creates a better experience for our users. Our team reflects and upholds our mission to level the playing field by presenting opportunities for careers in the arts to creatives from diverse backgrounds in all corners of the world.

We offer benefits including health insurance (vision and dental available), 401K, and tickets/tuition for select conferences/courses.

Title: Product Analyst - Remote
Description:
Who We Are:

Kasa is building a global accommodations brand unlike any other. We took the best that hotels and short-term rentals had to offer and created a new class of hospitality that is well priced, trustworthy, and that offers a large selection of great locations. Our guests enjoy seamless check-ins, spacious apartments, and attractive amenities, helping them feel right at home. If anything comes up, our remote guest experience team is available 24/7, ensuring our hospitality is always felt, though rarely seen.

Behind the scenes, we build technology that combines with our innovative operations to grow a globally scalable offering that delivers high-quality stays. Our products and systems unlock unparalleled flexibility to operate anywhere from a few Kasa to a few hundred Kasas in any type of building, in just about any location. We currently have Kasas in over 17 states and are expanding into new markets all the time.

All of this is made possible by our team members, each of whom plays a critical role in fulfilling our vision and mission. We strive to foster a culture that values feedback, support, and collaboration throughout the organization. As a remote-first company, we work hard to bridge the gap of distance through initiatives that foster connection across Kasa. A few examples include lively All-Hands meetings, department get-togethers (online and in-person), and teamwide celebrations of important milestones. We offer benefits that encourage team members to stay at Kasa properties to experience our product firsthand and meet local team members when nearby. Guests are crucial to Kasa's mission. Accordingly, every new Kasa team member gets trained in our Guest Experience Akademy during their onboarding.

Our team is fortunate to have diverse backgrounds, personalities, and experiences united by a commitment to excellence and passion for our industry. If Kasa's vision and culture speak to you, and you're up for the challenge of building a company on the cutting edge of real estate, we would love to have you on our team!

This role is fully remote, we set a location because some job boards require it.

The Role

We are looking for our first Product Analyst to drive a data-first culture across our Tech & Product team. We strive to understand what drives customer behavior across our product, which features have the highest impact and inform what to build next. With our team still in the foundational stage of product analytics, this role will continue laying the groundwork for measurement, experimentation and opportunity assessment of all Product work.

In this role, you will partner with a team of world-class Product Managers and Engineers to prioritize and measure the work we ship. You will report to the Sr Director, Product & Operations (CEO direct report) and work closely with the Business Operations team.

Possible upward trajectories from this role include senior analytic roles or Product Management.

About The Team

You will formally sit within the Product function at Kasa. Our Product & Technology team is split between the Bay Area, Hungary, and a few remote US locations.

Our PMs and engineers have diverse backgrounds in hospitality, consulting, real estate and technology. Everyone joined Kasa because they are passionate about building a platform that delivers value to landlords and serves guests seeking trustworthy, well-priced accommodations in great locations.

In addition, you will engage with analysts on our Business Intelligence function on the Business Operations team. These data wizards will partner on data pipelines, visualization, and more. Finally, you will interface with engineers for infrastructural data requirements.

Day in the life of a Kasa Product Analyst

Drawing on a range of data streams (and many more that still need to be added!), our Product Analyst will unearth insights and reveal the associated business and product implications. We want you to deeply understand what's happening in our product and how these relate to our company objectives. Combined, you'll propose opportunities for future feature development and measure the efficacy of solutions in flight.

Projects will require you to (1) Analyze, (2) Tell the Story: what happened and why, and (3) Recommend: what we should do based on these insights.
Develop and maintain Guest and Operator-facing metrics and dashboards in Looker for Kasa's Product teams, in addition to ad hoc analysis to help drive strategic business decisions.
Develop a deep understanding of our customer journeys (across guests, partners and internal teams), measured by key business metrics
Perform analytical deep-dives to analyze problems and opportunities, identify the hypothesis and design & execute experiments
Inform future experimentation design and roadmaps by performing exploratory analysis to understand user engagement behaviour and derive insights
Identify key trends and build executive-facing dashboards to track the progress of acquisition, monetization, and engagement trends.
Extract meaningful insights through analyzing large, complex, multi-dimensional customer behavior data sets
Set-up and assess multiple product experiments simultaneously
Translate complex concepts into implications for the business via excellent communication skills, both verbal and written


Experience
Bachelors' or above in quantitative field: Statistics, Applied Mathematics, Economics, Computer Science, Engineering, related field or equivalent experience.
4-6 years experience using analytics to drive key business decisions; examples include business/product/marketing analytics, business intelligence, strategy consulting
Proven track record of being able to work independently and proactively engage with business partners with minimal direction
Proficiency with SQL and comfort writing queries
Familiarity with data visualization tools like Looker or Tableau
Strong verbal and written communication skills

Plus if...
Experience building dashboards and analyzing data within Looker
Experience with front-end web analytical tools like Amplitude, Pendo or Heap (Alternatively: Google Analytics, Mixpanel, etc.)
Proficiency in programming/scripting like R or Python is a plus
You've worked in the hospitality industry at some point in your career
You've worked for small and large enterprise companies

In one year, you will succeed at Kasa by having:
Understood the guest, landlord and operating team product challenges facing companies in the furnished hospitality space
Worked with Product Managers to define and refine the metrics we use to measure progress against our team and business objectives, sharing these in a public, easy-to-consume format
Leveraged data to surface multiple high-impact opportunities that lead to product change and yield the intended effect


Benefits
🌏 Remote Work: With flexibility as a core value, and over three-quarters of the team working remotely, Kasa employees are able to work from anywhere!
✈ Kasa Travel Credit: We love to travel! Kasa employees get an allowance of free stays with us in any of our locations, plus a 50% discount on any nights for friends and family
📈 Generous Stock Option Plan: We believe the success of our business should be shared with our team. As you grow with us, we increase the opportunities for you to become part-owners of our company.
🙌 Flexible PTO: Full-time exempt Kasa employees are encouraged to take time off as they need and see fit, ensuring that it's not disruptive to their work
🏋️ Leadership coaching: Growth mindset is a core value for Kasa. One of the ways we deliver on it is by offering complimentary external leadership coaching to Kasa team members.
📈 401(k) plan: As you invest in yourself and your future, Kasa invests in you too: we match 50% of the first 4% of deferred salary.
💰 Competitive Salary: We offer base salaries at or above market rates plus additional earning opportunities based on the position
🩺 Health Coverage: We've invested in comprehensive health insurance options to help when you need it most


Kasa is an Equal Opportunity Employer. We do not discriminate on the basis of race, religion, color, sex, gender identity, sexual orientation, age, non-disqualifying physical or mental disability, national origin, veteran status, or any other basis covered by law. All employment is decided on the basis of qualifications, merit, and business need.

Title: Data Insights Analyst
Description:
Founded in 2016 by childhood friends and business partners Ryan Hogan and Derrick Smith, Hunt A Killer is a fast-growing entertainment company that disrupts conventional storytelling and delivers immersive, interactive entertainment experiences to over 100,000 subscribers worldwide. 

Hunt A Killer started as a single event, blending the concepts of escape room, interactive theater and live entertainment by immersing participants in a 200-acre living crime scene. From that first foray into entertainment we learned invaluable lessons, including how to truly immerse our audience in our experiences and the importance of learning from our audience. Hunt A Killer pivoted in October 2016 and launched our flagship monthly subscription box to 56 subscribers. Hunt A Killer has continued to learn and grow, evolving its products and distribution model to double our business year-over-year. Today we ship 150,000 episodic and complete mystery game boxes direct to consumers each month and sell purpose-built games through retail channels. In 2019, Hunt A Killer was named one of Fast Company’s World’s Most Innovative Companies, and in 2020, we placed 6th in the INC 5000 Fastest-Growing Companies.

Hunt A Killer is now working on additional ways to distribute its revolutionary content including licensing and digital channels, so that even more people can experience our stories. With this in mind and a course set for the horizon, we continue building a diverse team of creative decision-makers.  

Hunt A Killer is committed to bringing together individuals from different backgrounds and perspectives. We strive to create an inclusive environment where everyone can thrive, feel a sense of belonging, and do great work together. Our goal is to build a great team – with a great team, we can accomplish anything!

ABOUT THE ROLE
A successful Data Insights Analyst will be able to strike a balance between strategy and execution to ultimately deliver best-in-class insights to our internal clients. We’re looking for a bright and curious individual who enjoys uncovering actionable insights through data exploration and optimized data visualization. The ideal data generalist is a passionate self-starter who operates comfortably with ambiguity and can navigate complex challenges with minimal oversight.

LOCATION
We encourage candidates near both Baltimore, MD and Seattle, WA to apply!

YOU'RE THRILLED ABOUT THIS ROLE BECAUSE YOU WILL
Help the cross-functional teams make data-driven decisions, better understand trends and find key areas for efficiencies
Leverage Hunt A Killer’s agglomeration of data (both mobile and non-mobile) to identify trends, marketable insights and customer issues
Lend your data defined expertise to support our Business Intelligence ecosystem and showcase capabilities for growth focused insights presented in an easily digestible way
Drive the ongoing improvement and updating of reporting whether it be dashboards, retrospective reports or targeted analysis so business stakeholders have a complete and timely understanding of key metrics
Develop a deep understanding of consumer behaviors and how they engage with our products
Translate complex data from multiple sources to identify emerging and developing trends
Think creatively to tackle issues and develop actionable solutions

WE'RE THRILLED TO WELCOME YOU TO THE TEAM BECAUSE YOU HAVE
Bachelor’s preferably in Business, Economics, Mathematics/Statistics or related field
4+ years of experience in data analysis roles or quantitative field
Proven track record of working with large datasets, with an emphasis on analysis, data story-telling and visualization
Exceptional ability to take initiative, implement processes and accountability
Functional understanding of digital data collection and website tagging infrastructure
Deep experience with mobile application analytics
Demonstrated advanced Excel and data modeling skills
Expertise in Adobe Analytics and/or Google Analytics
Effective interpersonal skills to partner with cross-functional teams including remote colleagues
A detail-oriented curiosity to solve problems and communicate outcomes

Nice to Haves:
Experience in leveraging BI front-end tools like PowerBI or Tableau for clear data visualization insights
Proficiency in A/B testing, optimization and customer insights reporting
Prior experience in strategy or management consulting roles
Strong analytical skills and data-driven approach; ability to measure the impact of project deliverables
Other skills: PowerPivot, PowerQuery, DAX (Data Analysis Expressions) and programming languages (SQL, R and or Python) to explore and analyze data

YOU'LL LOVE HUNT A KILLER BECAUSE WE
Are passionate about innovations in entertainment and are obsessed with member satisfaction
Offer competitive compensation, comprehensive health, dental and vision, and 401k with matching
Believe in time off, and encourage as much
Solve complex problems on a daily basis

Hunt a Killer is an EOE M/F/D/V.

Title: DAT Data Analytics and Processing Engineer
Description:
At Ford Motor Company, we believe freedom of movement drives human progress. We also believe in providing you with the freedom to define and realize your dreams. With our incredible plans for the future of mobility, we have a wide variety of opportunities for you to accelerate your career potential as you help us define tomorrow’s transportation.

Do you have what it takes to make smart vehicles for a smart world? Join the Ford Product Development team. Utilizing Design Thinking and User Experience methods, you will work to deliver breakthrough products and services that delight our customers. We are seeking forward-thinking, laser-focused professionals with a passion for bringing innovative, exciting and sustainable ideas to life. We have opportunities around the world for you to contribute to such advancements as autonomy, electrification, smart mobility technologies and more!

What You Will Be Able To Do

Seeking an Engineer to lead the development and maintenance of the data processing, analytics, reporting strategy for Active Safety and Driver Assistance Systems features/technologies and real-world validation test data. You will:
Lead efficient data processing and analytics reporting of real-world data collection drives for use by various feature teams
Develop and implement methodology for placing the data into a structured format that allows for rapid analysis by data analysts using outstanding analytics tools (e.g. Tableau, QlikView, etc.)
Work with feature/function owners and V&V teams to understand metrics, use-cases and develop and refine tools/scripts to detect/trace requirement failures and problematic scenarios in real-world data
Understand, quantify and supervise the flow of data end-to-end from the test vehicle through data analysis to evaluate the processing chain for bottlenecks and efficiency improvements
Support sign-off of Feature Level performance for a given vehicle through data exploration and analysis of data conducted from real world evaluation drives
Build custom scripts to consume/partition data for specific use-cases needed by various feature owners (e.g. pre-collision assist data separate from adaptive cruise control data, etc.)
Visualize processing workflow and data statistics/reports using outstanding analytics tools (e.g. Tableau, QlikView, etc.)
Collaborate with team to develop an automated data processing chain to support data analysis, event review and issue generation (e.g. JIRA, etc.) activity
Work with suppliers to integrate internal processes with other data collection systems to ensure data associated with identified issues can be provided to the supplier and supervised end-to-end
Support design verification plans by analyzing resulting data and delivering reports and/or dashboards showing results and compliance with internal and external requirements
Develop innovative methods for analysis of Ford’s Advanced Driver Assistance System (ADAS) features
The minimum requirements we seek
Bachelor’s Degree in Engineering, Computer Science or Data Science
1+ year of experience developing and/or maintaining data processes, data analysis and/or dashboard analytics
Our preferred requirements
Master’s Degree in Electrical, Mechanical, Aerospace, Controls, Computer or Software Engineering, Computer Science, or Data Science
5+ years of experience in data operations, data analysis or data engineering
Developing reports and dashboards using Excel, Tableau, QlikView, Alteryx or other industry standard tools
Strong understanding of test statistics and analysis
Experience with Big Data, Data Warehousing and Database industry standard tools
Experience with Advanced Driver Assistance Systems features (e.g. Adaptive Cruise Control, Pre-Collision Assist, Park Assist, etc.)
Experience with remote sensing systems (e.g. Radar, Lidar, Vision Cameras, GPS/GNSS systems with maps, Vehicle to Vehicle Communications, etc.)
Software engineering and development experience
Any development time in any language (e.g. C, C++, Python, Matlab, Simulink, etc.)
Excellent communication and time management skills
Ability to work within a fast paced, team environment
What You Will Receive In Return

As part of the Ford family, you will enjoy excellent compensation and a comprehensive benefits package that includes generous PTO, retirement, savings and stock investment plans, incentive compensation and much more. You will also experience exciting opportunities for professional and personal growth and recognition.

If you have what it takes to help us redefine the future of mobility, we would love to have you join us.

Job Description


Join BAE Systems' Intelligence and Security Sector and be part of an agile team that enables our employees to support our customers and their missions. As a Data Analyst, you will apply statistics, machine learning, and analytic approaches to produce products supporting the mission. You will also use machine learning techniques to find hidden patterns, trends, classifiers, and anomalies. This position will provide the analyst with an opportunity to work alongside other data scientists and engineers to develop tools and process for analysis – and author SOPs. Products and processes may be brief to customer senior leadership, making a true impact for the warfighter.

May require TDY over life of the contract.

Other possible locations include Virginia, Georgia, North Carolina, Texas, Hawaii, Maryland, Germany, Italy, and South Korea. Please go to https://jobs.baesystems.com to apply for these locations.

Required Education, Experience, & Skills
BS in Data Science, Statistics, Applied Math, or related discipline and minimum 1 year of relevant experience or AA with 3 years of relevant experience.
Proficiency with R or Python, and SQL, AWS applications.
Experience implementing supervised and unsupervised machine learning techniques, statistical techniques and concepts, data retrieval and storage, visualization and warehousing, and extract-transform-load (ETL) processes.
Background in visualizing/presenting data for stakeholders and Knowledge of data visualization tools.

Preferred Education, Experience, & Skills
Five years intelligence analysis experience (MOS 35/350 series or other DoD/IC equivalent)

About BAE Systems Intelligence & Security
BAE Systems, Inc. is the U.S. subsidiary of BAE Systems plc, an international defense, aerospace and security company which delivers a full range of products and services for air, land and naval forces, as well as advanced electronics, security, information technology solutions and customer support services. Improving the future and protecting lives is an ambitious mission, but it’s what we do at BAE Systems. Working here means using your passion and ingenuity where it counts – defending national security with breakthrough technology, superior products, and intelligence solutions. As you develop the latest technology and defend national security, you will continually hone your skills on a team—making a big impact on a global scale. At BAE Systems, you’ll find a rewarding career that truly makes a difference.

Intelligence & Security (I&S), based in McLean, Virginia, designs and delivers advanced defense, intelligence, and security solutions that support the important missions of our customers. Our pride and dedication shows in everything we do—from intelligence analysis, cyber operations and IT expertise to systems development, systems integration, and operations and maintenance services. Knowing that our work enables the U.S. military and government to recognize, manage and defeat threats inspires us to push ourselves and our technologies to new levels.

At BAE Systems, we celebrate the array of skills, experiences, and perspectives our employees bring to the table. For us, differences are a source of strength. We’re laser-focused on high performance, and we work hard every day to nurture an inclusive culture where all employees can innovate and thrive. Here, you will not only build your career, but you will also enjoy work-life balance, uncover new experiences, and collaborate with passionate colleagues.

 Generate financial and statistical reporting by obtaining data from disparate sources ensuring the applicability and accuracy of the information.

Demonstrated experience in healthcare determining when vendors can augment and support company projects and work by defining requirements then selecting and working with vendors and service providers.
Must be available for limited travel as needed.
